10.title: Customs item detail section of CUSDEC
10.description: Group 23 to 33 of CUSDEC message.

11.title: Customs sub-item detail section of CUSDEC
11.description: Group 34 and 35 of CUSDEC message.

1.title: Included in document/transaction
1.description: The document line is included in the document/transaction.

2.title: Excluded from document/transaction
2.description: The document line is excluded from the document/transaction.

12.title: Telephone directory
12.description: Self explanatory.

16.title: Postcode directory
16.description: [3251] Code defining postal zones or addresses.

23.title: Clearing house automated payment
23.description: Self explanatory.

25.title: Bank identification
25.description: Code for identification of banks.

35.title: Rail additional charges
35.description: Self explanatory.

36.title: Railways networks
36.description: Self explanatory.

37.title: Railway locations
37.description: Code identifying a location in railway environment.

38.title: Rail customers
38.description: Self explanatory.

39.title: Rail unified nomenclature of goods
39.description: Self explanatory.

42.title: Business function
42.description: Self explanatory.

43.title: Clearing House Interbank Payment System Participants ID
43.description: Participants identification of the automated clearing house of the New York Clearing House Association (CHIPS).

44.title: Clearing House Interbank Payment System Universal ID
44.description: Universal identification of the automated clearing house of the New York Clearing House Association (CHIPS).

45.title: United Nations Common Coding System (UNCCS)
45.description: A code list adopted by the United Nations Organisations for the procurement of goods and services.

46.title: DUNS (Dun and Bradstreet) +4
46.description: An organization identified by the DUNS number and a 4- character extension.

54.title: Statistical object
54.description: A statistical object such as a statistical concept, array structure component or statistical nomenclature.

55.title: Quality conformance
55.description: A code list specifying the quality standard a product complies with, e.g. ISO9000, BS5750, etc.

56.title: Safety regulation
56.description: A code list specifying the safety regulations which apply to a product, such as UK COSHH (control of substances hazardous to health) regulations.

57.title: Product code
57.description: Code assigned to a specific product by a controlling agency.

58.title: Business account number
58.description: An identifying number or code assigned by issuing authorities to manage business activities.

59.title: Railway services harmonized code
59.description: Services provided by the different railway organizations.

60.title: Type of financial account
60.description: Identification of the type of financial account.

61.title: Type of assets and liabilities
61.description: Identification of the type of assets and liabilities.

62.title: Requirements indicator
62.description: A code list which specifies various requirements that a customer may have when fulfilling a purchase order.

67.title: Type of package
67.description: Indication of the type of package codes.

68.title: Type of industrial activity
68.description: Identification of the type of industrial activity.

69.title: Type of survey question
69.description: Identification of the type of survey question.

70.title: Customs inspection type
70.description: A code to indicate the type of inspection performed by customs.

71.title: Nature of transaction
71.description: Identification of the nature of the transaction.

104.title: Customs area of transaction
104.description: Customs code to indicate the different types of declarations according to the countries involved in the transaction (e.g. box 1/1 of SAD: inter EC Member States, EC-EFTA, EC-third countries, etc.).

105.title: Customs declaration type
105.description: Customs code to indicate the type of declaration according to the different Customs procedures requested (e.g.: import, export, transit).

106.title: Incoterms 1980
106.description: (4110) Code to indicate applicable Incoterm (1980 edition) under which seller undertakes to deliver merchandise to buyer (ICC). Incoterms 1990: use 4053 only.

107.title: Excise duty
107.description: Customs or fiscal authorities code to identify a specific or ad valorem levy on a specific commodity, applied either domestically or at time of importation.

109.title: Customs indicator
109.description: Customs code for circumstances where only an indication is needed.

110.title: Customs special codes
110.description: Customs code to indicate an exemption to a regulation or a special Customs treatment.

112.title: Statistical nature of transaction
112.description: Indication of the type of contract under which goods are supplied.

113.title: Customs office
113.description: Customs administrative unit competent for the performance of Customs formalities, and the premises or other areas approved for the purpose by the competent authorities (CCC).

114.title: Railcar letter marking
114.description: Codes for all marking codes (in letters) for railcars specifying the type, series, order number, check digit and some technical characteristics.

115.title: Examination facility
115.description: Building or location where merchandise is examined by Customs.

116.title: Customs preference
116.description: Customs code to identify a specific tariff preference.

117.title: Customs procedure
117.description: (9380) Customs code to identify goods which are subject to Customs control (e.g. home use, Customs warehousing, temporary admission, Customs transit).

118.title: Government agency procedure
118.description: Treatment applied by a government agency other than Customs to merchandise under their control.

119.title: Customs simplified procedure
119.description: Customs code to indicate the type of simplified Customs procedure requested by a declarant (CCC).

120.title: Customs status of goods
120.description: Customs code to specify the status accorded by Customs to a consignment e.g. release without further formality, present supporting documents for inspection, etc (CCC).

121.title: Shipment description
121.description: Code to indicate whether a shipment is a total, part or split consignment.

122.title: Commodity
122.description: (7357) Code identifying types of goods for Customs, transport or statistical purposes (generic term).

123.title: Entitlement
123.description: Code to indicate the recipient of a charge amount (IATA).

125.title: Customs transit guarantee
125.description: Customs code to identify the type of guarantee used in a transit movement.

126.title: Accounting information identifier
126.description: Identification of a specific kind of accounting information.

127.title: Customs valuation method
127.description: Customs code to identify the valuation method used to determine the dutiable value of the declared goods.

129.title: Customs warehouse
129.description: Identification and/or location of the Customs warehouse in which goods will be or have been deposited (CCC).

130.title: Special handling
130.description: Code to indicate that the nature of the consignment may necessitate use of special handling procedures (IATA).

131.title: Free zone
131.description: Code identifying the zone within a state where any goods introduced are generally regarded, insofar as import duties and taxes are concerned, as being outside the Customs territory and are not subject to the usual Customs control.

132.title: Charge
132.description: Identification of a type of charge.

133.title: Financial regime
133.description: Nature and methods of a transaction from financial viewpoint.

134.title: Duty, tax or fee payment method
134.description: [4390] Method by which a duty or tax is paid to the relevant administration.

135.title: Rate class
135.description: Code to identify a specific rate category.

136.title: Restrictions/prohibitions on re-use of certain wagons

139.title: Port
139.description: A location having facilities for means of transport to load or discharge cargo.

140.title: Area
140.description: Codes for specific geographic areas e.g. seas, straits, basins etc.

143.title: Removable accessories and special equipment on railcars

145.title: Airport/city
145.description: As described and published by IATA.

146.title: Means of transport identification
146.description: Code identifying the name or number of a means of transport (vessel, vehicle).

147.title: Document requested by Customs
147.description: Customs code to identify documents requested by Customs in an information interchange.

148.title: Customs release notification
148.description: Authorisation given by Customs to move the goods or not move the goods from the place of registration.

149.title: Customs transit type
149.description: Customs code to indicate the different kinds of transit movement of the goods (e.g. Box 1/3 of the SAD).

154.title: Bank branch sorting identification
154.description: Identification of a specific branch of a bank.

156.title: Location of goods
156.description: (3384) Indication of the place where goods are located and where they are available for examination.

157.title: Clearing code
157.description: Identification of the responsible bank/clearing house which has cleared or is ordered to do the clearing.

158.title: Terms of delivery
158.description: Code to identify terms of delivery.

161.title: Goods description
161.description: Identification of a type of goods description.

163.title: Country sub-entity
163.description: (3228) Identification of country sub-entity (region, department, state, province) defined by appropriate authority.

165.title: Amendment code (Customs)
165.description: Customs code indicating the reason for transmitting an amendment to Customs.

166.title: Social security identification
166.description: Code assigned by the authority competent to issue social security identification to identify a person.

167.title: Tax party identification
167.description: Code assigned by a tax authority to identify a party.

169.title: Harmonized system
169.description: Identification of commodities according to the Harmonized System.

173.title: Export requirements
173.description: Identification of requirements and regulations established by relevant authorities concerning exportation.

176.title: Flow of the goods
176.description: List of statistical codes covering the movement of the goods to be declared (e.g. despatch, arrival).

177.title: Statistical procedures
177.description: Indication of the statistical procedure to which the goods are subject.

178.title: Standard text according US embargo regulations
178.description: US government regulations prescribe specific standard text usage. Using codes from this code list prevents full text transmission.

179.title: Standard text for export according national prescriptions
179.description: National export regulations prescribe specific standard text usage. Using codes from this code list prevents full text transmission.

180.title: Airport terminal
180.description: Code identifying terminals or other sub-locations at airports.

182.title: Combiterms 1990
182.description: Code to indicate the applicable Combiterm (1990 edition), used for the purpose of cost distribution between seller according to Incoterms 1990.

183.title: Dangerous goods packing type
183.description: Identification of package types for the description related to dangerous goods.

184.title: Tax assessment method
184.description: A code to identify the tax assessment method.

185.title: Item type
185.description: A code list defining the level of elaboration of a item such as raw material, component, tooling, etc.

186.title: Product supply condition
186.description: A code list specifying the rules according to which a product is supplied, e.g. from stock, available on demand, make on order, etc.

187.title: Supplier's stock turnover
187.description: A code list giving an indication about the level of the supplier's stock turnover.

188.title: Article status
188.description: A code list defining the status of an article from the procurement point of view, e.g. new article, critical article, etc.

189.title: Quality control code
189.description: A code list specifying how the article is classified according to the quality control point of view, e.g. safety item, subject to regulation, etc.

190.title: Item sourcing category
190.description: A code list to specify details related to the sourcing of the corresponding item such as provided by the buyer, from a mandatory source, etc.

191.title: Dumping or countervailing assessment method
191.description: A code to identify the method used to determine the dumping or countervailing duty.

192.title: Dumping specification
192.description: Code list to identify types of goods for dumping purposes.

AAA.title: Acknowledgement of order number
AAA.description: [1018] Reference number assigned by the seller to his acknowledgement of an order.

AAB.title: Proforma invoice number
AAB.description: [1088] Reference number assigned by the seller to a Proforma Invoice.

AAC.title: Documentary credit number
AAC.description: [1172] Reference number assigned by issuing bank to a Documentary credit.

AAD.title: Contract addendum number
AAD.description: [1318] Reference number assigned by the issuer to a Contract Addendum.

AAE.title: Goods declaration number
AAE.description: Reference number assigned to a goods declaration.

AAG.title: Offer number
AAG.description: Reference number assigned by issuing party to an offer.

AAJ.title: Delivery order number
AAJ.description: Reference number assigned by issuer to a delivery order.

AAK.title: Despatch advice number
AAK.description: Reference number assigned by issuing party to a despatch advice.

AAL.title: Drawing number
AAL.description: Reference number identifying a specific product drawing.

AAM.title: Waybill number
AAM.description: Reference number assigned to a waybill, see: 1001 = 700.

AAN.title: Delivery schedule number
AAN.description: Reference number assigned by buyer to a delivery schedule.

AAO.title: Consignee's shipment reference number
AAO.description: [1362] Reference assigned by the consignee to a shipment.

AAP.title: Part consignment number
AAP.description: [1310] Reference to a specific consignment forming part of a contract allowing part deliveries.

AAQ.title: Unit load device (e.g. container) identification number
AAQ.description: [8260] Marks (letters and/or numbers) which identify a unit load device e.g. freight container.

AAS.title: Transport document number
AAS.description: [1188] Reference assigned by the carrier or his agent to the transport document.

AAT.title: Master label number
AAT.description: Identifies the master label number of any package type.

AAU.title: Despatch note number
AAU.description: [1128] Reference number assigned by the seller to a Despatch Note.

AAV.title: Enquiry number
AAV.description: Reference number assigned to an enquiry.

AAY.title: Carrier's agent reference number
AAY.description: Reference number assigned by the carriers agent to a transaction.

AAZ.title: Standard Carrier Alpha Code (SCAC) number
AAZ.description: For maritime shipments, this code qualifies a Standard Alpha Carrier Code (SCAC) as issued by the United Stated National Motor Traffic Association Inc.

ABA.title: Customs valuation decision number
ABA.description: Reference by an importing party to a previous decision made by a Customs administration regarding the valuation of goods.

ABB.title: End use authorization number
ABB.description: Reference issued by a Customs administration authorizing a preferential rate of duty if a product is used for a specified purpose, see: 1001 = 990.

ABC.title: Anti-dumping case number
ABC.description: Reference issued by a Customs administration pertaining to a past or current investigation of goods "dumped" at a price lower than the exporter's domestic market price.

ABD.title: Customs tariff number
ABD.description: [7282] Code number of the goods in accordance with the tariff nomenclature system of classification in use where the Customs declaration is made.

ABE.title: Declarant's reference number
ABE.description: Unique reference number assigned to a document or a message by the declarant for identification purposes.

ABG.title: Customs decision request number
ABG.description: Reference issued by Customs pertaining to a pending tariff classification decision requested by an importer or agent.

ABH.title: Sub-house bill of lading number
ABH.description: Reference assigned to a sub-house bill of lading.

ABI.title: Deferred payment reference
ABI.description: [1168] Reference or indication of the deferred payment of duty/tax.

ABJ.title: Quota number
ABJ.description: Reference number allocated by a government authority to identify a quota.

ABK.title: Transit (onward carriage) guarantee (bond) number
ABK.description: Reference number to identify the guarantee or security provided for Customs transit operation (CCC).

ABL.title: Customs guarantee number
ABL.description: Reference assigned to a Customs guarantee.

ABP.title: Declarant's Customs identity number
ABP.description: Reference to the party whose posted bond or security is being declared in order to accept responsibility for a goods declaration and the applicable duties and taxes.

ABQ.title: Importer reference number
ABQ.description: Reference number assigned by the importer to identify a particular shipment for his own purposes.

ABR.title: Export clearance instruction reference number
ABR.description: Reference number of the clearance instructions given by the consignor through different means.

ABS.title: Import clearance instruction reference number
ABS.description: Reference number of the import clearance instructions given by the consignor/consignee through different means.

ABT.title: Customs declaration number
ABT.description: [1426] Number, assigned or accepted by Customs, to identify a Goods declaration.

AB.title: Text Element Identifier deletion reference
AB.description: The reference used within a given TEI (Text Element Identifier) which is to be deleted.

ABY.title: Allotment identification (Air)
ABY.description: Reference assigned to guarantied capacity on one or more specific flights on specific date(s) to third parties as agents and other airlines.

ABZ.title: Vehicle licence number
ABZ.description: Number of the licence issued for a vehicle by an agency of government.

AC.title: Air cargo transfer manifest Banker's acceptance
AC.description: Description to be provided. Reference number for banker's acceptance issued by the accepting financial institution.

ACA.title: Cargo acceptance order reference number
ACA.description: Reference assigned to the cargo acceptance order.

ACC.title: Shipping unit identification
ACC.description: Identifying marks on the outermost unit that is used to transport merchandise.

ACD.title: Additional reference number
ACD.description: Reference number provided in addition to another given reference.

ACG.title: ATA carnet number
ACG.description: Reference number assigned to an ATA carnet.

ACI.title: Outerpackaging unit identification
ACI.description: (7070) Identifying marks on packing units contained within an outermost shipping unit.

ACJ.title: Customer material specification number
ACJ.description: Number for a material specification given by customer.

ACK.title: Bank reference
ACK.description: Cross reference issued by financial institution.

ACM.title: Unique REINAC reference number of the sender

ACN.title: Advice of collection number
ACN.description: [1030] Number of the Advice of Collection attached to the Rail Consignment Note (CIM 75).

ACO.title: Iron charge number
ACO.description: Number attributed to the iron charge for the production of steel products.

ACP.title: Hot roll number
ACP.description: Number attributed to a hot roll coil.

ACQ.title: Cold roll number
ACQ.description: Number attributed to a cold roll coil.

ACR.title: Railway wagon number
ACR.description: (8320) Registered identification initials and numbers of railway wagon. Synonym: Rail car number.

ACS.title: Unique CURRAC reference number of the sender

ACT.title: Unique claims reference number of the sender

ACU.title: Loss/event number
ACU.description: To reference to the unique number that is assigned to each major loss hitting the reinsurance industry.

ACV.title: Estimate order reference number
ACV.description: Reference number assigned by the ordering party of the estimate order.

ACW.title: Reference number to previous message
ACW.description: Reference number assigned to the message which was previously issued (e.g. in the case of a cancellation, the primary reference of the message to be cancelled will be quoted in this element).

ACY.title: Duty memo number
ACY.description: Reference number assigned by customs to a duty memo.

ACZ.title: Equipment transport charge number
ACZ.description: Reference assigned to a specific equipment transportation charge.

ADA.title: Buyer's item number
ADA.description: Reference number assigned by the buyer to an item.

ADB.title: Matured certificate of deposit
ADB.description: Reference number for certificate of deposit allocated by issuing financial institution.

ADC.title: Loan
ADC.description: Reference number for loan allocated by lending financial institution.

ADD.title: Analysis number/test number
ADD.description: Number given to a specific analysis or test operation.

ADL.title: Ordering customer consignment reference number
ADL.description: Reference number assigned to the consignment by the ordering customer.

ADM.title: Shipowner's authorization number
ADM.description: Reference number assigned by the shipowner as an authorization number to transport certain goods (such as hazardous goods, cool or reefer goods).

ADN.title: Inland transport order number
ADN.description: Reference number assigned by the principal to the transport order for inland carriage.

ADO.title: Container work order reference number
ADO.description: Reference number assigned by the principal to the work order for a (set of) container(s).

ADY.title: Report number
ADY.description: Reference to a report to Customs by a carrier at the point of entry, encompassing both conveyance and consignment information.

ADZ.title: Trader account number
ADZ.description: Number assigned by a Customs authority which uniquely identifies a trader (i.e. importer, exporter or declarant) for Customs purposes.

AE.title: Authorization for expense (AFE) number Non-negotiable maritime transport document number
AE.description: Description to be provided. Reference number assigned to a sea waybill, see: 1001 = 712.

AEA.title: Government agency reference number
AEA.description: Coded reference number that pertains to the business of a government agency.

AEE.title: Eur 1 certificate number
AEE.description: Reference number assigned to a Eur 1 certificate.

AEF.title: Customer process specification number
AEF.description: Retrieval number for a process specification defined by customer.

AEG.title: Customer specification number
AEG.description: Retrieval number for a specification defined by customer.

AEH.title: Applicable instructions or standards
AEH.description: Instructions or standards applicable for the whole message or a message line item. These instructions or standards may be published by a neutral organization or authority or another party concerned.

AEI.title: Registration number of previous Customs declaration
AEI.description: Registration number of the Customs declaration lodged for the previous Customs procedure.

AEJ.title: Post-entry reference
AEJ.description: Reference to a message related to a post-entry.

AEL.title: Delivery number (transport)
AEL.description: Reference number by which a haulier/carrier will announce himself at the container terminal or depot when delivering equipment.

AEM.title: Transport route
AEM.description: A predefined and identified sequence of points where goods are collected, agreed between partners, e.g. the party in charge of organizing the transport and the parties where goods will be collected. The same collecting points may be included in different transport routes, but in a different sequence.

AEN.title: Customer's unit inventory number
AEN.description: Number assigned by customer to a unique unit for inventory purposes.

AEO.title: Product reservation number
AEO.description: Number assigned by seller to identify reservation of specified products.

AEP.title: Project number
AEP.description: Reference number assigned to a project.

AEQ.title: Drawing list number
AEQ.description: Reference number identifying a drawing list.

AER.title: Project specification number
AER.description: Reference number identifying a project specification.

AEU.title: Supplier's control number
AEU.description: Reference to a file regarding a control of the supplier carried out on departure of the goods.

AEV.title: Shipping note number
AEV.description: Reference number assigned to a shipping note, see: 1001 = 630.

AEW.title: Empty container bill number
AEW.description: Reference number assigned to an empty container bill, see: 1001 = 708.

AEY.title: Substitute air waybill number
AEY.description: Reference number assigned to a substitute air waybill, see: 1001 = 743.

AEZ.title: Despatch note (post parcels) number
AEZ.description: (1128) Reference number assigned to a despatch note (post parcels), see: 1001 = 750.

AF.title: Airlines flight identification number Bill of quantities number
AF.description: (8110) Identification of a commercial flight by carrier code and number as assigned by the airline (IATA). Reference number assigned to a bill of quantities.

AFA.title: Through bill of lading number
AFA.description: Reference number assigned to a through bill of lading, see: 1001 = 761.

AFB.title: Cargo manifest number
AFB.description: Reference number assigned to a cargo manifest, see: 1001 = 785.

AFC.title: Bordereau number
AFC.description: Reference number assigned to a bordereau, see: 1001 = 787.

AFD.title: Customs item number
AFD.description: Number (1496 in CST) assigned by the declarant to an item.

AFE.title: Export Control Commodity number (ECCN)
AFE.description: Reference number to relevant item within Commodity Control List covering actual products change functionality.

AFF.title: Marking/label reference
AFF.description: Reference where marking/label information derives from.

AFH.title: Replenishment purchase order number
AFH.description: Purchase order number specified by the buyer for the assignment to vendor's replenishment orders in a vendor managed inventory program.

AFI.title: Immediate transportation no. for in bond movement

AFJ.title: Transportation exportation no. for in bond movement

AFK.title: Immediate exportation no. for in bond movement

AFQ.title: Applicant's bank reference
AFQ.description: Reference number of the applicant's bank.

AFR.title: Issuing bank's reference
AFR.description: Reference number of the issuing bank.

AFS.title: Beneficiary's bank reference
AFS.description: Reference number of the beneficiary's bank.

AFT.title: Direct payment valuation number
AFT.description: Reference number assigned to a direct payment valuation.

AFU.title: Direct payment valuation request number
AFU.description: Reference number assigned to a direct payment valuation request.

AFV.title: Quantity valuation number
AFV.description: Reference number assigned to a quantity valuation.

AFW.title: Quantity valuation request number
AFW.description: Reference number assigned to a quantity valuation request.

AFY.title: Payment valuation number
AFY.description: Reference number assigned to a payment valuation.

AFZ.title: Situation number
AFZ.description: Common reference number given to documents concerning a determined period of works.

AGB.title: Contract party reference number
AGB.description: Reference number assigned to a party for a particular contract.

AGC.title: Account party's bank reference
AGC.description: Reference number of the account party's bank.

AGD.title: Agent's bank reference
AGD.description: Reference number issued by the agent's bank.

AGG.title: Dispute number
AGG.description: Reference number to a dispute notice.

AGH.title: Credit rating agency's reference number
AGH.description: Reference number assigned by a credit rating agency to a debtor.

AGL.title: Delivery verification certificate
AGL.description: Formal identification of delivery verification certificate which is a formal document from Customs etc. confirming that physical goods have been delivered. It may be needed to support a tax reclaim based on an invoice.

AGM.title: Number of temporary importation document
AGM.description: Number assigned by customs to identify consignment in transit.

AGN.title: Reference number quoted on statement
AGN.description: Reference number quoted on the statement sent to the beneficiary for information purposes.

AGO.title: Sender's reference to the original message
AGO.description: The reference provided by the sender of the original message.

AGP.title: Company issued equipment ID
AGP.description: Owner/operator, non-government issued equipment reference number.

AGQ.title: Domestic flight number
AGQ.description: Airline flight number assigned to a flight originating and terminating within the same country.

AGR.title: International flight number
AGR.description: Airline flight number assigned to a flight originating and terminating across national borders.

REN.description: [1150] Number assigned to a rail consignment upon its arrival at its destination station (CIM 84).

RF.title: Export reference number
RF.description: Reference number given to an export shipment.

RR.title: Payer's financial institution transit routing No.(ACH transfers)

RT.title: Payee's financial institution transit routing No.

SA.title: Sales person number
SA.description: Identification number of a sales person.

SE.title: Serial number
SE.description: Identification number of an item which distinguishes this specific item out of an number of identical items.

SH.title: Previous highest schedule number
SH.description: Number of the latest schedule of a previous period (ODETTE DELINS).

SN.title: Seal number
SN.description: [9308] Identification number on Customs or other seals affixed to containers or other transport units.

SRN.title: Shipment reference number
SRN.description: [1140] Reference number assigned by a consignor to a particular shipment for his own purposes or for those of the consignee.

SS.title: Sellers reference number
SS.description: Reference number assigned to a transaction by the seller.

STA.title: Station reference number
STA.description: International UIC code assigned to every European rail station (CIM convention).

SW.title: Swap order number
SW.description: Number assigned by the seller to a swap order (see definition of DE 1001, code 229).

SZ.title: Specification number
SZ.description: Number assigned by the issuer to his specification.

TB.title: Trucker's bill of lading
TB.description: A cargo list/description issued by a motor carrier of freight.

TE.title: Telex message number
TE.description: Reference number identifying a telex message.

TF.title: Transfer number
TF.description: An extra number assigned to goods or a container which functions as a reference number or as an authorization number to get the goods or container released from a certain party.

TI.title: TIR carnet number
TI.description: Reference number assigned to a TIR carnet.

TL.title: Tax exemption licence number
TL.description: Number assigned by the tax authorities to a party indicating its tax exemption authorization. This number could relate to a specified business type, a specified local area or a class of products.

TN.title: Transaction reference number
TN.description: Reference applied to a transaction between two or more parties over a defined life cycle; e.g. number applied by importer or broker to obtain release from Customs, may then used to control declaration through final accounting (synonyms: declaration, entry number).

TP.title: Test report number
TP.description: Reference number identifying a test report document relevant to the product.

UAR.title: Upper serial number of range
UAR.description: Upper serial number in a range for declaration of incoming goods.

UC.title: Ultimate customer's reference number
UC.description: The originator's reference number as forwarded in a sequence of parties involved.

UCN.title: Unique consignment reference number
UCN.description: (1202) Unique reference of a consignment (UCRN) used for identification purposes in documents and messages exchanged between parties in international trade. See also: Unique Identifier Code (UNIC) in UN/ECE Recommendation No. 8, March 1992.

UN.title: United Nations dangerous goods (UNDG) number
UN.description: [7124] Unique serial number assigned within the United Nations to substances and articles contained in a list of the dangerous goods most commonly carried.

UO.title: Ultimate customer's order number
UO.description: The originator's order number as forwarded in a sequence of parties involved.

VA.title: VAT registration number
VA.description: Unique number assigned by the relevant tax authority to identify a party for use in relation to Value Added Tax (VAT).

VC.title: Vendor contract number
VC.description: Number assigned by the vendor to a contract.

VM.title: Vessel identification
VM.description: (8123) Reference identifying a vessel (UN/ECE Recommendation No 10).

VN.title: Order number (vendor)
VN.description: Reference number assigned by supplier to a buyer's purchase order.

VON.title: Voyage number
VON.description: [8228] Reference number assigned by the carrier or his agent to the voyage of the vessel.

VP.title: Vendor product number
VP.description: Number assigned by vendor to another manufacturer's product.

VT.title: Motor vehicle identification number
VT.description: (Reference identifying a motor vehicle used for transport) normally is the vehicle registration number.

WE.title: Warehouse entry number
WE.description: Entry number under which imported merchandise was placed in a Customs bonded warehouse.

A.title: Company/place registration number
A.description: Company registration and place as legally required.

C.title: Cargo control number
C.description: Reference used to identify and control a carrier and consignment from initial entry into a country until release of the cargo by Customs.

P.title: Previous cargo control number
P.description: Where a consignment is deconsolidated and/or transferred to the control of another carrier or freight forwarder (e.g. housebill, abstract) this references the previous (e.g. master) cargo control number.

2.title: Broadcast 2

4.description: The plant requesting the delivery of an item assigns a number indicating the sequence of the finished article.

5.title: Transmission sequence
5.description: The positional sequence when transmitted.

6.title: Structure sequence
6.description: The positional sequence in a message structure as published in a particular UN directory.

3.description: Message containing items (e.g. line items, goods items, Customs items, equipment items) to be deleted from a previously sent message.

4.description: Message containing items (e.g. line items, goods items, Customs items, equipment items) to be changed in a previously sent message.

5.title: Replace
5.description: Message replacing a previous message.

6.title: Confirmation
6.description: Message confirming the details of a previous transmission where such confirmation is required or recommended under the terms of a trading partner agreement.

7.title: Duplicate
7.description: The message is a duplicate of a previously generated message.

8.title: Status
8.description: Description to be provided.

9.title: Original
9.description: Initial transmission related to a given transaction.

10.title: Not found
10.description: Message whose reference number is not filed.

11.title: Response
11.description: Message responding to a previous message or document.

12.title: Not processed
12.description: Message indicating that the referenced message was received but not yet processed.

13.description: Self explanatory.

14.title: Advance notification
14.description: Self explanatory.

15.title: Reminder
15.description: Repeated message transmission for reminding purposes.

16.description: Message content is a proposal.

17.title: Cancel, to be reissued
17.description: Referenced transaction cancelled, reissued message will follow.

18.description: New issue of a previous message (maybe cancelled).

19.title: Seller initiated change
19.description: Change information submitted by buyer but initiated by seller.

20.title: Replace heading section only
20.description: Message to replace the heading of a previous message.

21.title: Replace item detail and summary only
21.description: Message to replace item detail and summary of a previous message.

22.description: Final message in a related series of messages together making up a commercial, administrative or transport transaction.

23.description: Message not to be processed until further release information.

24.description: Delivery schedule message only used to transmit short- term delivery instructions.

25.title: Forecast
25.description: Delivery schedule message only used to transmit long-term schedule information.

26.title: Delivery instruction and forecast
26.description: Combination of codes '24' and '25'.

27.description: Message to inform that the referenced message is not accepted by the recipient.

28.title: Accepted, with amendment in heading section
28.description: Message accepted but amended in heading section.

29.title: Accepted without amendment
29.description: Referenced message is entirely accepted.

30.title: Accepted, with amendment in detail section
30.description: Referenced message is accepted but amended in detail section.

31.description: Indicates that the message is a copy of an original message that has been sent, e.g. for action or information.

32.title: Approval
32.description: A message releasing an existing referenced message for action to the receiver.

33.title: Change in heading section
33.description: Message changing the referenced message heading section.

34.title: Accepted with amendment
34.description: The referenced message is accepted but amended.

35.title: Retransmission
35.description: Change-free transmission of a message previously sent.

36.title: Change in detail section
36.description: Message changing referenced detail section.

37.title: Reversal of a debit
37.description: Reversal of a previously posted debit.

38.title: Reversal of a credit
38.description: Reversal of a previously posted credit.

39.title: Reversal for cancellation
39.description: Description to be provided.

40.title: Request for deletion
40.description: The message is given to inform the recipient to delete the referenced transaction.

41.title: Finishing/closing order
41.description: Last of series of call-offs.

42.title: Confirmation via specific means
42.description: Message confirming a transaction previously agreed via other means (e.g. phone).

43.title: Additional transmission
43.description: Message already transmitted via another communication channel. This transmission is to provide electronically processable data only.

44.title: Accepted without reserves
44.description: Message accepted without reserves.

45.title: Accepted with reserves
45.description: Message accepted with reserves.

48.title: Accepted, contents rejected
48.description: Message to inform that the previous message is received, but it cannot be processed due to regulations, laws, etc.

50.title: Withdraw
50.description: Message withdrawing a previously approved message.

51.title: Authorisation
51.description: Message authorising a message or transaction(s).

52.title: Proposed amendment
52.description: A code used to indicate an amendment suggested by the sender.

53.title: Test
53.description: Code indicating the message is to be considered as a test.

55.title: Notification only
55.description: The receiver may use the notification information for analysis only.

The document can continue to be used for future declarations until the allowance is exhausted. The document is not attached to the declaration but has already been lodged in the Customs station.

708.description: Format of period to be given in actual message without hyphen.

717.description: Format of period to be given in actual message without hyphen.

718.description: Format of period to be given without hyphen.

811.description: To indicate a quantity of half months.

3.description: Payment time reference is date of contract.

4.description: Payment time reference is date of signature of contract.

5.description: Payment time reference is date of invoice.

8.description: Payment time reference is date of confirmation received.

9.description: Payment time reference is date of invoice received.

12.description: Payment time reference is date of present document received.

56.description: Payment time reference is date of receipt of tooling or set of tooling.

57.description: Payment time reference is date of acceptance of first samples produced under production conditions.

64.description: Date of certificate of temporary acceptance of work until final reception will take place.

72.description: Date when a payment was made.

76.description: Draft(s) is/are due after a specific number of days after date of presentation of documents.

79.description: Date when goods clear Customs in the exporting country.

81.description: Date of shipment as evidenced by the transport document(s).

AA.title: Party to be billed (AAR Accounting rule 11)
AA.description: Party to be billed in accordance with AAR Accounting rule 11.

AB.title: Buyer's agent/representative
AB.description: Third party who arranged the purchase of merchandise on behalf of the actual buyer.

AE.title: Declarant's agent/representative
AE.description: Any natural or legal person who makes a declaration to an official body on behalf of another natural or legal person, where legally permitted (CCC).

AF.title: Transit principal
AF.description: Natural or legal person responsible for the satisfactory performance of a Customs transit operation. Source: CCC.

AG.title: Agent/representative
AG.description: (3196) Party authorized to act on behalf of another party.

AH.title: Transit principal's agent/representative
AH.description: Agent acting on behalf of the transit principal (CCC).

AI.title: Successful job applicant
AI.description: Person who has been chosen for a job.

AJ.title: Party issuing mutually agreed codes
AJ.description: The party which has issued all mutually agreed codes used in the message.

AK.title: Acknowledgement recipient
AK.description: Party to whom acknowledgement should be sent.

AL.title: Principal
AL.description: (3340) Party accepting liability for goods held or moving (e.g. transit) under a Customs authorization and - when applicable - a guarantee.

AM.title: Authorized official
AM.description: Employee of a company or firm authorized to act on behalf of that company or firm e.g. to make a Customs declaration.

AN.title: Approved importer
AN.description: Person or company which is authorised by the relevant Customs authority to import goods without payment all taxes or specific taxes at the point of entry into the country.

AP.title: Accepting party
AP.description: (3352) Party accepting goods, products, services etc.

AQ.title: Approved consignor
AQ.description: Person or company approved by the relevant authority in the country to pack and export specific goods under Customs supervision.

AR.title: Authorized exporter
AR.description: Exporter authorized/approved by Customs for special Customs procedures e.g. simplified procedure.

AS.title: Account servicing financial institution
AS.description: Identifies the financial institution servicing the account(s).

AT.title: Authorized importer
AT.description: Importer authorized/approved by Customs for special Customs procedures e.g. simplified procedure.

AU.title: Authorized trader (transit)
AU.description: Trader authorized/approved by Customs for special transit procedures e.g. simplified procedure.

AV.title: Authorizing official
AV.description: Party that has delegated the authority to take a certain action on behalf of a company or agency.

AW.title: Applicant's bank
AW.description: Financial institution which is requested to issue the documentary credit.

A.title: Authenticating party
A.description: Party which certifies that a document is authentic.

AZ.title: Issuing bank
AZ.description: Financial institution which issues the documentary credit, if the applicant's bank is not acting as the issuing bank.

B1.title: Contact bank 1
B1.description: Identifies an additional bank which must be informed of certain aspects of the message.

B2.title: Contact bank 2
B2.description: Identifies an additional bank which must be informed of certain aspects of the message.

BA.title: Booking agent
BA.description: Party acting as a booking office for transport and forwarding services.

BB.title: Buyer's bank
BB.description: [3420] Bank employed by the buyer to make payment.

BC.title: Negotiating bank
BC.description: Financial institution to whom a negotiable documentary credit is directed.

BE.title: Beneficiary
BE.description: The ultimate recipient of the funds. Normally the account owner who is reimbursed by the payor.

BF.title: Beneficiary's bank
BF.description: Identifies the account servicer for the beneficiary or the payee.

BI.title: Buyer's financial institution
BI.description: Financial institution designated by buyer to make payment.

BJ.title: Release to party
BJ.description: Party to which the goods or container(s) is (are) to be released.

BM.title: Insured
BM.description: Party which is the object of an insurance contract.

BN.title: Insurance beneficiary
BN.description: Party which benefits from insurance coverage.

BO.title: Broker or sales office
BO.description: Party acting in the name of the seller as broker or as sales office.

BP.title: Building site purchaser
BP.description: Party at the building site responsible for the purchasing of goods and services for that particular site.

BQ.title: Cheque drawn bank
BQ.description: Identifies the bank on which the cheque should be drawn, as instructed by the ordering customer.

BS.title: Bill and ship to
BS.description: Party receiving goods and relevant invoice.

BT.title: Party to be billed for other than freight (bill to)
BT.description: Party receiving invoice excluding freight costs.

BU.title: Service bureau
BU.description: Party carrying out service bureau processing work, (e.g. a payroll bureau).

BV.title: Member
BV.description: Member of a group (e.g. of a group of persons or a service scheme).

B.title: Building site engineer
B.description: Party at the building site responsible for engineering matters for that particular site.

BY.title: Buyer
BY.description: (3002) Party to which merchandise is sold.

BZ.title: Building site forwarder
BZ.description: Party at the building site responsible for forwarding the received goods on that particular site.

CA.title: Carrier
CA.description: (3126) Party undertaking or arranging transport of goods between named points.

CB.title: Customs broker
CB.description: Agent or representative or a professional Customs clearing agent who deals directly with Customs on behalf of the importer or exporter (CCC).

CC.title: Claimant
CC.description: Party who claims goods or insurance.

CF.title: Container operator/lessee
CF.description: Party to whom the possession of specified property (e.g. container) has been conveyed for a period of time in return for rental payments.

CG.title: Carrier's agent
CG.description: Party authorized to act for or on behalf of carrier.

CH.title: Connecting carrier
CH.description: Owner or operator of a transportation conveyance to which goods in a given transaction will be transferred.

CI.title: Commission processor
CI.description: Party who provides extra treatment to goods on commission base.

CJ.title: Previous member
CJ.description: Previous member of a group of persons or a service scheme.

CK.title: Empty equipment despatch party
CK.description: Party from whose premises empty equipment will be or has been despatched.

CL.title: Container location party
CL.description: Party from whose premises container will be or has been despatched.

CM.title: Customs
CM.description: Identification of customs authority relevant to the transaction or shipment.

CN.title: Consignee
CN.description: (3132) Party to which goods are consigned.

CO.title: Corporate office
CO.description: Identification of the Head Office within a company.

COP.title: Convoying party
COP.description: Party designated to escort the transported goods.

CP.title: Party to receive certificate of compliance
CP.description: Party acting for or on behalf of seller in matters concerning compliance.

CPD.title: Charges payer at destination
CPD.description: Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges concerning the destination operations.

CQ.title: Cheque order
CQ.description: Party to which the cheque will be ordered, when different from the beneficiary.

CR.title: Empty equipment return party
CR.description: Party to whose premises empty equipment will be or has been returned.

CS.title: Consolidator
CS.description: Party consolidating various consignments, payments etc.

C.title: Consignee's agent
C.description: Party authorized to act on behalf of the consignee.

CY.title: Commissionable agent
CY.description: IATA cargo agent entitled to commission.

CZ.title: Consignor
CZ.description: (3336) Party which, by contract with a carrier, consigns or sends goods with the carrier, or has them conveyed by him. Synonym: shipper, sender.

DA.title: Available with bank (documentary credits)
DA.description: Financial institution with whom the documentary credit is available.

DB.title: Distributor branch
DB.description: The affiliate of a retailer or distributor.

DC.title: Deconsolidator
DC.description: Party that splits up a large consignment composed of separate consignments of goods. The smaller consignments of goods were grouped together into that large consignment for carriage as a larger unit in order to obtain a reduced rate.

DCP.title: Despatch charge payer
DCP.description: Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges concerning the despatch operations.

DD.title: Documentary credit account party's bank
DD.description: Bank of the documentary credit account party.

DE.title: Depositor
DE.description: Party depositing goods, financial payments or documents.

DF.title: Documentary credit applicant
DF.description: Party at whose request the applicant's bank/issuing bank is to issue a documentary credit.

DG.title: Documentary credit beneficiary
DG.description: Party in whose favour the documentary credit is to be issued and the party that must comply with the credit's terms and conditions.

DH.title: Documentary credit account party
DH.description: Party which is responsible for the payment settlement of the documentary credit with the applicant's bank/issuing bank, if different from the documentary credit applicant.

DI.title: Documentary credit second beneficiary
DI.description: Party to whom the documentary credit can be transferred.

DJ.title: Party according to documentary credit transaction
DJ.description: Party related to documentary credit transaction.

DK.title: Documentary credit beneficiary's bank
DK.description: Financial institution with which the beneficiary of the documentary credit maintains an account.

DL.title: Factor
DL.description: Company offering a financial service whereby a firm sells or transfers title to its accounts receivable to the factoring company.

DM.title: Party to whom documents are to be presented

DO.title: Document recipient
DO.description: (1370) Party which should receive a specified document.

DP.title: Delivery party
DP.description: (3144) Party to which goods should be delivered, if not identical with consignee.

DQ.title: Owner's agent
DQ.description: Person acting on delegation of powers of the owner.

DR.title: Driver
DR.description: Person who drives a means of transport.

DS.title: Distributor
DS.description: Party distributing goods, financial payments or documents.

DT.title: Declarant
DT.description: (3140) Party who makes a declaration to an official body or - where legally permitted - in whose name, or on whose behalf, a declaration to an official body is made.

DU.title: Owner's representative
DU.description: Person commissioned by the owner to represent him in certain circumstances.

DV.title: Project management office
DV.description: Party commissioned by the owner to follow through the execution of all works.

DW.title: Drawee
DW.description: Party on whom drafts must be drawn.

D.title: Engineer (construction)
D.description: Party representing the contractor to advise and supervise engineering aspects of the works.

DY.title: Engineer, resident (construction)
DY.description: Party commissioned by the owner to advise and supervise engineering aspects of the works.

EB.title: Building inspectorate
EB.description: Party controlling the conformity of works to legal and regulation rules.

EE.title: Location of goods for customs examination before clearance

EF.title: Project coordination office
EF.description: Party responsible for technical coordination of works.

EI.title: Controller, quality
EI.description: Party controlling the quality of goods and workmanship for the project.

EJ.title: Surveyor, quantity
EJ.description: Party responsible for the quantification and valuation of the works on behalf of the contractor.

EK.title: Surveyor (professional), quantity
EK.description: Party responsible to the owner for the quantification and valuation of the works.

EL.title: Project
EL.description: Party responsible for a project, e.g. a construction project.

EM.title: Party to receive electronic memo of invoice
EM.description: Party being informed about invoice issue (via EDI).

EN.title: Tenderer
EN.description: Firm answering an invitation to tender.

EQ.title: Empty container responsible party
EQ.description: Party responsible for the empty container.

ER.title: Empty container return agent
ER.description: Party, designated by owner of containers, responsible for their collection as agreed between the owner and customer/ consignee.

ES.title: Contractor, lead
ES.description: Leader representing a grouping of co-contractors.

ET.title: Co-contractor
ET.description: Member of a grouping of co-contractors.

EU.title: Contractor, general
EU.description: Single contractor for the whole construction project, working by his own or with subcontractors.

EV.title: Subcontractor
EV.description: Firm carrying out a part of the works for a contractor.

E.title: Exporter
E.description: (3030) Party who makes - or on whose behalf a Customs clearing agent or other authorized person makes - an export declaration. This may include a manufacturer, seller or other person. Within a Customs union, consignor may have the same meaning as exporter.

EY.title: Subcontractor, nominated
EY.description: Subcontractor authorized by the owner after having been proposed.

EZ.title: Operator, essential services
EZ.description: Operator of essential services e.g. water, sewerage system, power.

FB.title: Nominated freight company
FB.description: Party nominated to act as transport company or carrier for the goods.

FC.title: Contractor, main
FC.description: Firm or grouping of co-contractors which has been awarded the contract.

FF.title: Factor, correspondent
FF.description: Factoring company engaged by another factoring company to assist the letter with the services provided to the clients (sellers).

FG.title: Buyer as officially registered
FG.description: Buying party as officially registered with government.

FH.title: Seller as officially registered
FH.description: Selling party as officially registered with government.

FI.title: Copy message to
FI.description: Party that is to receive a copy of a message.

FK.title: Previous Trade Union
FK.description: Employee organisation who previously represented an employee .

FL.title: Passenger
FL.description: A person conveyed by a means of transport, other than the crew.

FM.title: Crew member
FM.description: A person manning a means of transport.

FN.title: Tariff issuer
FN.description: The issuer of a tariff, e.g. a freight tariff.

FP.title: Freight/charges payer
FP.description: Party responsible for the payment of freight.

FQ.title: Container survey agent
FQ.description: The container survey agency that will survey the containers.

FR.title: Message from
FR.description: Party where the message comes from.

FS.title: Party authorized to make definite a contract action
FS.description: Party who has the authority to make definite a contract action.

FT.title: Party responsible for financial settlement
FT.description: (3450) Party responsible for either the transfer or repatriation of the funds relating to a transaction.

FU.title: Hazardous material office
FU.description: The office responsible for providing information regarding hazardous material.

FV.title: Party providing government furnished property
FV.description: The party responsible for providing government furnished property.

F.title: Current receiver
F.description: Current receiver of the goods in a multi-step transportation process (indirect flow) involving at least one grouping centre.

FY.title: Current sender
FY.description: Current sender of the goods in a multi-step transportation process (indirect flow) involving at least one grouping centre.

FZ.title: Grouping centre
FZ.description: A party in charge of groupage, including degroupage and regroupage.

GB.title: Chamber of commerce
GB.description: Name of the Chamber of Commerce of the town where the company is registered.

GC.title: Goods custodian
GC.description: (3024) Party responsible for the keeping of goods.

GD.title: Producer
GD.description: Party or person who has produced the produce.

GE.title: Registration tribunal
GE.description: Name of the tribunal where the company is registered.

GF.title: Slot charter party
GF.description: An identification code of a participant or user that books slots (space) on a ship, more likely on a long term basis on a series of sailings. He pays for the space whether he uses it or not.

GG.title: Warehouse
GG.description: The name of the warehouse where product is held.

GH.title: Applicant for job
GH.description: A person who applied for a job.

GL.title: Socially insured person
GL.description: A person who is registered in a social security scheme.

GM.title: Inventory controller
GM.description: To specifically identify the party in charge of inventory control.

GN.title: Processor
GN.description: Party or person who has or will apply a process.

GO.title: Goods owner
GO.description: The party which owns the goods.

GP.title: Packer
GP.description: Party or person who has undertaken or will undertake packing.

GQ.title: Slaughterer
GQ.description: Party or person who has undertaken or will undertake a slaughter.

GR.title: Goods releaser
GR.description: (3026) Party entitled to authorize release of goods from custodian.

GS.title: Consignor's representative
GS.description: Party authorised to represent the consignor.

GT.title: Rail carrier
GT.description: A carrier moving cargo, including containers, via rail.

IU.description: Non-resident party who makes the payment or against whom a claim exists.

IV.description: (3006) Party to whom an invoice is issued.

IW.description: Non-resident party receiving the payment or against whom a liability exists.

LB.description: A code used to identify a party who participates in production.

MS.description: Issuer of a document and/or sender of a message.

NI.description: (3180) Party to be notified of arrival of goods.

RW.description: Party issuing the contract (waybill) for carriage.

SO.title: Sold to if different than bill to

SU.description: (3280) Party which manufactures or otherwise has possession of goods, and consigns or makes them available in trade.

S.description: Natural of legal person (generally a bank of insurance company) who accepts responsibility in due legal form for the financial guarantee to Customs of the payment of additional duties or fees that become due against a particular shipment, which have not previously been covered by surety.

SY.title: Surety
SY.description: Natural or legal person (generally a bank or insurance company) who accepts responsibility in due legal form for the financial consequences of non-fulfilment of another's obligations to the Customs (CCC).

SZ.title: Surety for antidumping/countervailing duty
SZ.description: Natural or legal person that has been contracted by the importer to guarantee to Customs the payment of antidumping and/or countervailing duties that become due against a particular shipment.

TCP.title: Transit charge payer
TCP.description: Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges concerning the transit operations.

TD.title: Party to receive technical documentation
TD.description: Party to whom technical documentation should be sent.

TR.title: Terminal operator
TR.description: A party which handles the loading and unloading of marine vessels.

TS.title: Party to receive certified test results
TS.description: Party to whom the certified test results should be sent.

UC.title: Ultimate consignee
UC.description: Party who has been designated on the invoice or packing list as the final recipient of the stated merchandise.

UHP.description: Party authorized (during a voyage) to apply unexpected handling procedures or party having applied these procedures.

WD.description: (3004) Party depositing goods in a warehouse.

WH.description: (3022) Party taking responsibility for goods entered into a warehouse.

WPA.description: Party designated (legally accepted) to ascertain the weight.
