CG.description: Head of unit to contact for matters regarding dissemination of information.

CN.title: Consignee
CN.description: (3132) Party to which goods are consigned.

CO.title: Consignor
CO.description: (3336) Party which, by contract with a carrier, consigns or sends goods with the carrier, or has them conveyed by him. Synonym: shipper/sender.

CP.title: Responsible person for computer data processing
CP.description: Responsible person to contact for matters regarding computer data processing.

CW.title: Confirmed with
CW.description: Person with whom the contents of the purchase order has been discussed and agreed (e.g. by telephone) prior to the sending of this message.

EB.title: Entered by
EB.description: Name of an individual who made the entry.

EC.title: Education coordinator
EC.description: Person in charge of coordination of education.

ED.title: Engineering contact
ED.description: Department/person to contact for matters regarding engineering.

E.title: Expeditor
E.description: Party to be contacted where goods are (to be) expedited.

GR.title: Goods receiving contact
GR.description: Department/person responsible for receiving the goods at the place of delivery.

HE.title: Emergency dangerous goods contact
HE.description: Party who is to be contacted to intervene in case of emergency.

HG.title: Dangerous goods contact
HG.description: Department/person to be contacted for details about the transportation of dangerous goods/hazardous material.

HM.title: Hazardous material contact
HM.description: Department/person responsible for hazardous material control.

IC.title: Information contact
IC.description: Department/person to contact for questions regarding transactions.

MC.title: Material control contact
MC.description: Department/person responsible for the controlling/inspection of goods.

MD.title: Material disposition contact
MD.description: Department/person responsible for the disposition/scheduling of goods.

OC.title: Order contact
OC.description: An individual to contact for questions regarding this order.

PD.title: Purchasing contact
PD.description: Department/person responsible for issuing this purchase order.

PM.title: Product management contact
PM.description: Department/person to contact for questions regarding this order.

QA.title: Quality assurance contact
QA.description: Quality assurance contact within an organization.

QC.title: Quality coordinator contact
QC.description: Quality coordinator contact within an organization.

RD.title: Receiving dock contact
RD.description: The receiving dock contact within an organization.

SA.title: Sales administration
SA.description: Name of the sales administration contact within a corporation.

SC.title: Schedule contact
SC.description: Name of the scheduling contact within a corporation.

SD.title: Shipping contact
SD.description: The shipping department contact within an organization.

SR.title: Sales representative or department
SR.description: The sales representative or department contact within an organization.

SU.title: Supplier contact
SU.description: Department/person to be contacted at the supplier.

TA.title: Traffic administrator
TA.description: The traffic administrator contact within an organization.

WH.title: Warehouse
WH.description: The warehouse contact within an organization.

AA.title: Circuit switching
AA.description: A process that, on demand, connects two or more data terminal equipments and permits the exclusive use of a data circuit between them until the connection is released (ISO).

AB.title: SITA
AB.description: Communications number assigned by Societe Internationale de Telecommunications Aeronautiques (SITA).

AC.title: ARINC
AC.description: Communications number assigned by Aeronautical Radio Inc.

AD.title: Courier
AD.description: A communication channel identifying a courier.

EI.title: EDI transmission
EI.description: Number identifying the service and service user.

EM.title: Electronic mail
EM.description: Creating/sending/receiving of unstructured free text messages or documents using computer network, a mini- computer or an attached modem and regular telephone line or other electronic transmission media.

F.title: Telefax X.400
F.description: Device used for transmitting and reproducing fixed graphic material (as printing) by means of signals over telephone lines or other electronic transmission media. CCITT Message handling system.

PS.title: Packet switching
PS.description: The process of routing and transferring data by means of addressed packets so that a channel is occupied only during the transmission; upon completion of the transmission the channel is made available for the transfer of other packets (ISO).

SW.title: S.W.I.F.T.
SW.description: Communications address assigned by Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunications s.c.

TT.title: Teletext
TT.description: Transmission of text/data via teletext. Communication service involving Teletypewriter machines connected by wire or electronic transmission media. Teletypewriter machines are the devices used to send and receive signals and produce hardcopy from them.

AA.title: Circuit switching
AA.description: A process that, on demand, connects two or more data terminal equipments and permits the exclusive use of a data circuit between them until the connection is released (ISO).

AB.title: SITA
AB.description: Communications number assigned by Societe Internationale de Telecommunications Aeronautiques (SITA).

AC.title: ARINC
AC.description: Communications number assigned by Aeronautical Radio Inc.

AF.title: U.S. Defense Switched Network
AF.description: The switched telecommunications network of the United States Department of Defense.

AG.title: U.S. federal telecommunications system
AG.description: The switched telecommunications network of the United States government.

EI.title: EDI transmission
EI.description: Number identifying the service and service user.

EM.title: Electronic mail
EM.description: Creating/sending/receiving of unstructured free text messages or documents using computer network, a mini- computer or an attached modem and regular telephone line or other electronic transmission media.

F.title: Telefax X.400
F.description: Device used for transmitting and reproducing fixed graphic material (as printing) by means of signals over telephone lines or other electronic transmission media. CCITT Message handling system.

PS.title: Packet switching
PS.description: The process of routing and transferring data by means of addressed packets so that a channel is occupied only during the transmission; upon completion of the transmission the channel is made available for the transfer of other packets (ISO).

SW.title: S.W.I.F.T.
SW.description: Communications address assigned by Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunications s.c.

TT.title: Teletext
TT.description: Transmission of text/data via teletext. Communication service involving Teletypewriter machines connected by wire or electronic transmission media. Teletypewriter machines are the devices used to send and receive signals and produce hardcopy from them.

1.title: Place of terms of delivery
1.description: (3018) Point or port of departure, shipment or destination, as required under the applicable terms of delivery, e.g. Incoterms.

2.title: Payment place
2.description: Place where funds are to be, or have been made available to the creditor.

4.title: Goods receipt place
4.description: Place at which the goods have been received by the consignee.

5.title: Place of departure
5.description: (3214) Port, airport or other location from which a means of transport is scheduled to depart or has departed.

7.title: Place of delivery
7.description: (3246) Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

8.title: Place of destination
8.description: Port, airport or other location to which a means of transport is destined.

9.title: Place/port of loading
9.description: (3334 + 3230) Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are loaded on to the means of transport being used for their carriage.

10.title: Place of acceptance
10.description: (3348) Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier.

11.title: Place/port of discharge
11.description: (3392 + 3414) Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are unloaded from the means of transport having been used for their carriage.

12.title: Port of discharge
12.description: Port at which the goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

13.title: Place of transhipment
13.description: (3424) Place where goods are transferred from one means of transport to another (operational term).

14.title: Location of goods
14.description: (3384) Place where goods are located and where they are available for examination.

15.title: Place of transfer responsibility
15.description: Place where the responsibility for the goods under transport is transferred.

16.title: Place of transfer of ownership
16.description: Place where the ownership of the goods is transferred.

17.title: Border crossing place
17.description: Place where goods are transported across a country border.

18.title: Warehouse
18.description: (3156) Warehouse where a particular consignment has been stored.

19.title: Factory/plant
19.description: Factory/plant relevant for a particular consignment.

20.title: Place of ultimate destination of goods
20.description: Place where goods will ultimately be delivered.

21.title: Terms of sale place
21.description: Place of departure, shipment or destination as specified in the terms of sale agreed between the parties.

22.title: Customs office of clearance
22.description: (3080) Place where Customs clearance procedure occur (CCC).

23.title: Port of release
23.description: Port where goods are released from Customs custody.

24.title: Port of entry
24.description: Port where final documentation is filed for Customs Entry processing.

25.title: Country
25.description: Country relevant for a particular transaction.

26.title: City
26.description: City or town relevant for a particular transaction or consignment.

27.title: Country of origin
27.description: [3238] Country in which the goods have been produced or manufactured, according to criteria laid down for the purposes of application of the Customs tariff, of quantitative restrictions, or of any other measure related to trade.

28.title: Country of destination of goods
28.description: Country to which the goods are to be delivered.

29.title: Railway station
29.description: Name or identification of a railway station/yard relevant to a particular consignment.

30.title: Country of source
30.description: Country in which raw material or components were originally produced prior to manufacture or assembly in another country.

31.title: Building
31.description: A building or part thereof relevant to a particular consignment or transaction.

32.title: Beginning of chargeable section
32.description: First rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

33.title: Baseport of discharge
33.description: The port of discharge according to the tariff as opposed to the operational port of discharge. The goods may or may not be actually discharged at that port on the main transport.

34.title: Baseport of loading
34.description: The port of loading according to the tariff as opposed to the operational port of loading. The goods may or may not be actually loaded at that port on the main transport.

35.title: Country of exportation/despatch
35.description: (3220) Country from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Syn.: country whence consigned. Country of despatch: country from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

36.title: Country of ultimate destination
36.description: (3216) Country known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final country to which the goods are to be delivered.

37.title: Country of last consignment
37.description: [3331] Country where the goods are loaded onto the means of transport used for their importation.

38.title: Country of first destination
38.description: [3219] Country where the goods are offloaded from the means of transport used for their exportation.

39.title: Country of production
39.description: Country where item has been or will be produced.

40.title: Country of trading
40.description: Country where item has been or will be traded.

41.title: Customs office of entry
41.description: [3088] Customs office at which the goods enter the country of destination.

42.title: Customs office of exit
42.description: [3096] Customs office at which the goods leave the country of dispatch/export.

43.title: Place of Customs examination
43.description: Place where Customs undertakes a physical inspection of goods to satisfy themselves that the goods' nature, origin, condition, quantity and value are in accordance with the particulars furnished on the goods declaration (CCC).

44.title: Place of authentication of document
44.description: (3410) Place where document is signed or otherwise authenticated. Synonym: Place of issue of document.

45.title: Customs office of destination (transit)
45.description: (3086) Customs office at which a transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Customs office of transit termination.

46.title: Region of despatch
46.description: Region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

47.title: Region of destination
47.description: Region known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final region to which the goods are to be delivered.

48.title: Region of production
48.description: Region where item has been or will be produced.

50.title: Customs office of transit
50.description: [3106] Customs office which is competent for transit formalities en route.

51.title: Country of invalid transit guarantee
51.description: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is not valid.

52.title: Country of destination (transit)
52.description: Country at which a Customs transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Country of transit termination.

53.title: Charge and freight due from
53.description: Place or point from which charges and freight are charged.

54.title: Manufacturing department
54.description: A department within the manufacturing area (e.g. lacquering, assembly).

55.title: Charges and freight payable to
55.description: [3274] Name of place up to which freight charges and other charges are to be paid.

56.title: End of chargeable section
56.description: Last rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

57.title: Place of payment
57.description: Name of the location at which freight and charges for main transport are payable.

58.title: Full track loading or unloading
58.description: Identification of the station proceeding to the loading or unloading of a rail wagon on a full track site. (Used only when a rail station is obliged to transfer the load on another wagon for technical reasons - e.g. damage).

60.title: Place of arrival
60.description: Place at which the transport means arrives.

61.title: Next port of call
61.description: Next port which the vessel is going to call upon.

62.title: On-carriage port
62.description: Port of discharge at which the cargo is discharged from the vessel, used for transport after the main transport (transit port).

64.title: First optional place of discharge
64.description: The first optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

65.title: Final port or place of discharge
65.description: Name of the seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are finally (to be) unloaded from the means of transport used for their carriage according to the transport contract.

66.title: Express railway station
66.description: Railway station offering express transportation services.

67.title: Mixed cargo railway station
67.description: Railway station offering mixed cargo transportation services .

68.title: Second optional place of discharge
68.description: The second optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of shipper.

69.title: Next non-discharge port of call
69.description: A code to identify the next port of call for a vessel where no cargo will be discharged.

70.title: Third optional place of discharge
70.description: The third optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

71.title: Reconsolidation point
71.description: A place where cargo is reconsolidated.

72.title: Fourth optional place of discharge
72.description: The fourth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

73.title: Bill of lading release office
73.description: A location where bills of lading are released to customers.

74.title: Transhipment excluding this place
74.description: Place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is not authorised.

75.title: Transhipment limited to this place
75.description: Only place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is authorised.

76.title: Original port of loading
76.description: The port where the goods were first loaded on a vessel.

77.title: First port of call - non-discharging
77.description: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will not be discharging cargoes.

78.title: First port of call - discharging
78.description: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will be discharging cargoes.

79.title: Place/port of first entry
79.description: Place or port where final documentation is filed for Customs Entry processing.

80.title: Place of despatch
80.description: Place at which the goods are taken over for carriage (operational term), if different from the transport contract place of acceptance (see: 10). Synonym: Place of origin of carriage.

81.title: Fifth optional place of discharge
81.description: The fifth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

82.title: Pre-carriage port
82.description: Port of loading at which the cargo is loaded on the pre- carriage vessel used for the transport prior to the main transport.

83.title: Place of delivery (by on carriage)
83.description: Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered.

84.title: Transport contract place of acceptance
84.description: Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier according to the contract of carriage.

85.title: Transport contract place of destination
85.description: Place to which the goods are destined.

86.title: Country of valid transit guarantee
86.description: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is valid.

87.title: Place/port of conveyance initial arrival
87.description: Place/port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the "Last place/port of call of conveyance" (125).

88.title: Place of receipt
88.description: Identification of the location at which the cargo is actually received.

89.title: Place of registration
89.description: Place where a means of transport is officially registered.

90.title: Place/location where special treatments have happened or must happen

91.title: Place of document issue
91.description: The place or location where a document is issued.

93.title: Station of application of additional costs
93.description: Rail station where, according to the transport contract, some chargeable operations must happen (re-weighting, re- fixing of the load, control on equipment and on consignment, etc.).

94.title: Previous port of call
94.description: Previous port which the vessel has called upon.

95.title: Sailing destination area
95.description: Geographical area to which the vessel's trip is destined.

96.title: Place of lodgement of documents
96.description: Customs station where, required documents for Customs declarations, have been lodged.

97.title: Optional place of discharge
97.description: The optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the bill of lading where cargo is discharged at the option of the shipper.

98.title: Place of empty equipment despatch
98.description: The location from which empty equipment is despatched.

99.title: Place of empty equipment return
99.description: The location to which empty equipment is returned.

100.title: Place/port of warehouse entry
100.description: Location (e.g. district) within a Customs territory where a warehouse entry was filed to enter merchandise into a Customs bonded warehouse.

101.title: Country of first sale
101.description: Name of country where firstly a sale took place.

102.title: Country of purchase
102.description: [3394] Country where the importer's co-contractor is domiciled or has his business.

103.title: Place of transfer
103.description: Place at which goods are transferred from one carrier to another (contractual term).

104.title: Place of deconsolidation
104.description: Place where a large consignment is de-grouped into smaller consignments.

105.title: Place of consumption
105.description: Place/location where goods enter the marketplace (commerce) of the importing country.

106.title: Region of origin
106.description: Region in which the goods have been produced or manufactured according to the criteria laid down for the purposes of the application of the Customs tariff, of quantitative restrictions or of any other measures related to trade (see: 3238).

107.title: Place of consolidation
107.description: Place where smaller consignments of goods are grouped together into a large consignment to be transported as a larger unit.

108.title: Rate combination point
108.description: Point over which sector rates are combined.

109.title: Place of prolongation decision of delivery delay
109.description: Place where it has been decided to prolong the delivery delay.

110.title: Recharging place/location
110.description: Place/location where a consignment has been changed of destination and is subject to a recharge note. (Complementary orders to modify the routing of the transport may be given, upon which a new charge calculation may be applied by the carrier).

111.title: Customs office of despatch
111.description: Customs office from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

112.title: Region of equipment availability
112.description: Region in which a piece of equipment is requested to be made available for on-hire.

113.title: Country of despatch
113.description: Country from which goods are despatched within a Customs union.

114.title: Customs office of export
114.description: Customs office from which goods are taken out of the Customs territory (CCC).

115.title: Free zone of export
115.description: Foreign free zone (desc: see 1131 = 131) from which goods are exported to the country of importation.

116.title: Region of export/despatch
116.description: Region from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Region of despatch: region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

117.title: Place of collection
117.description: Place where goods are to be or could be picked up (collected).

118.title: Customs office of departure
118.description: Customs office at which a Customs transit operation commences (CCC).

119.title: Customs office of transit guarantee
119.description: [3110] Customs office at which a security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is lodged.

120.title: Country of transhipment
120.description: Country where goods are transferred under Customs control from the importing means of transport to the exporting means of transport within the area of one Customs office which is the office of both importation and exportation (CCC).

121.title: Country of sale
121.description: [3116] Country where exporter's co-contractor is domiciled or has his business.

122.title: Customs office of destination
122.description: Customs office where the goods are to be cleared (CCC).

125.title: Last place/port of call of conveyance
125.description: Conveyance departed from this last foreign place/port of call to go to "Place/port of conveyance initial arrival" (87).

126.title: Country of previous Customs procedure
126.description: Country in which the Customs declaration for the previous Customs procedure has been lodged.

127.title: Customs office of registration of previous Customs declaration
127.description: Customs office where the previous Customs declaration has been lodged.

128.title: Participant sender location
128.description: Place where a participant in the movement of goods is located and can be contacted.

129.title: Wage negotiation district
129.description: The district to which workers belong for the purposes of union wage negotiation.

130.title: Place of ultimate destination of conveyance
130.description: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place to which a means of transport is ultimately destined.

131.title: Place of loading of empty equipment
131.description: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was loaded onto means of transport.

132.title: Place of discharge of empty equipment
132.description: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was unloaded from means of transport.

133.title: Region of delivery
133.description: (3246) Region to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

134.title: Petroleum warehouse
134.description: Bonded petroleum warehouse or the supplier source.

135.title: Place of entry (Customs)
135.description: Place at which the goods enter the Customs territory.

136.title: Living animals care place
136.description: Place where living animal cares are provided.

137.title: Re-icing place
137.description: Place where re-icing must be executed.

138.title: Weighting place
138.description: Place where weight can be ascertained.

139.title: Marshalling yard
139.description: Station where the wagons are disconnected and reconnected to form a new train.

140.title: Shopping station
140.description: Station where the train must stop or is stopped for unexpected handling.

141.title: Loading dock
141.description: Platform specially equipped for loading and unloading of rail wagons.

142.title: Port connection
142.description: Track connecting a rail station to a dock.

143.title: Place of expiry
143.description: Place where the documentary credit expires for presentation of required documents.

144.title: Place of negotiation
144.description: Place where the documentary credit is to be presented for negotiation.

145.title: Claims payable place
145.description: Place where insurance claims are payable.

146.title: Documentary credit available in
146.description: Place where the documentary credit is available with any bank.

147.title: Stowage cell
147.description: Location on a vessel where units can be stowed.

148.title: For transportation to
148.description: Place/country where goods are to be transported to.

149.title: Loading on board/despatch/taking in charge at/from
149.description: Place/country where goods have to be loaded on board, despatched or taken in charge.

150.title: Container stack position
150.description: Stack position of a container at a terminal, depot or freight station.

151.title: Private box
151.description: A private box used for pick-up and delivery of packages, e.g. of express packages.

152.title: Next port of discharge
152.description: Next port at which goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

153.title: Port of call
153.description: Port where a vessel has called upon or will call upon.

154.title: Place/location of on-hire
154.description: Place/location where an object is contracted for use.

155.title: Place/location of off-hire
155.description: Place/location where an object's contract for use ends.

156.title: Other carriers terminal
156.description: A carrier terminal belonging to a carrier other than the original carrier.

157.title: Country of Value Added Tax (VAT) jurisdiction
157.description: The country governing the VAT regulation to which the transaction is subject.

158.title: Contact location
158.description: The site where a contact is located.

159.title: Additional internal destination
159.description: Any location within the consignee's premises where the goods are moved to.

160.title: Foreign port of call
160.description: A code to identify the foreign port where the vessel calls at or will call at.

161.title: Maintenance location
161.description: A location where maintenance has been or will be performed.

162.title: Place or location of sale
162.description: Place or location at which the sale takes place.

163.title: Direct investment country
163.description: Country in which a direct investment is made or withdrawn.

164.title: Berth
164.description: Place or location in a port where a vessel is moored.

165.title: Construction country
165.description: Country in which the construction work is made.

166.title: Donation acting country
166.description: Country acting in the donation of aid.

167.title: Payment transaction country
167.description: Country of the foreign counterpart of the payment transaction.

168.title: Physical place of return of item
168.description: Physical place at which the item is returned, i.e. the location where the supplier receives the item form the customer.

169.title: Relay port
169.description: A location where cargo is transferred from one ocean carrier's vessel to another vessel owned or operated by the same carrier under the same bill of lading.

170.title: Final port of discharge
170.description: Last port at which cargo is unloaded from a vessel before the cargo is moved to a place of delivery or destination.

171.title: Place of destination for pre-stacking prior to stowage
171.description: The destination location for which items are to be pre- stacked prior to being stowed together on a means of transport.

172.title: Reporting location
172.description: The location to which the information being reported is applicable.

ZZZ.title: Mutually defined
ZZZ.description: Place or location as agreed between the relevant parties.

1.title: Bore
1.description: Self explanatory. Self explanatory. Self explanatory.

4.title: Centre
4.description: Self explanatory.

5.title: Core
5.description: Self explanatory.

6.title: Surface
6.description: Self explanatory.

7.title: Beginning
7.description: The sample is taken at the beginning of the specimen. The sample is taken at the end of the specimen.

9.title: Middle
9.description: The sample is taken at the middle of the specimen.

10.title: Centre Back
10.description: The sample location is centre across width, back end across length.

11.title: Centre front
11.description: The sample location is centre across width, front end across length.

12.title: Centre middle
12.description: The sample location is centre across width, middle end across length.

13.title: Edge back
13.description: The sample location is on the edge across width, back end across length.

14.title: Edge front
14.description: The sample location is on the edge across width, front end across length.

15.title: Edge middle
15.description: The sample location is on the edge across the width, middle end across length.

16.title: Quarter back
16.description: The sample location is a quarter way across the width, back end across length.

17.title: Quarter front
17.description: The sample location is a quarter way across the width, front end across length.

18.title: Quarter middle
18.description: The sample location is a quarter way across the width, middle end across length.

19.title: Weld
19.description: The sample is taken from the weld of the specimen.

20.title: Body
20.description: Sample is taken from the body of the specimen.

DO.title: Domestic
DO.description: Domestic message as defined by relevant central bank.

DR.title: Domestic with regulatory information required
DR.description: Domestic message with requirement to regulatory information to central bank.

EA.title: Economic area
EA.description: Message crossing at least one national boundary but confined within a specific economic area (e.g. EC, EFTA ...).

IN.title: International
IN.description: International message as defined by relevant central bank.

IR.title: International with regulatory information required
IR.description: International message with requirement to regulatory information to central bank.

1.title: Applicant's bank
1.description: The financial institution which is requested to issue the documentary credit.

2.title: Issuing bank
2.description: The financial institution which issues the documentary credit, if the applicant's bank is not acting as the issuing bank.

3.title: Beneficiary's bank

12.title: Non-dutiable
12.description: Reference to an allowance or charge as being free for Customs duty computation purposes.

13.title: All charges borne by payee
13.description: All charges are to be borne by the beneficiary.

14.title: Each pay own cost
14.description: Each party are to be responsible for its own charges.

15.title: All charges borne by payor
15.description: All the charges are to be borne by the ordering customer.

16.description: All bank charges associated with a documentary credit are to be borne by the applicant.

17.title: All bank charges except confirmation commission to be borne by applicant
17.description: All bank charges associated with a documentary credit except confirmation commission are to borne by the applicant.

18.description: All bank charges associated with a documentary credit are to be borne by the beneficiary.

21.title: Amendment charges to be borne by beneficiary
21.description: Documentary credit amendment charges are to be borne by the beneficiary.

23.title: Discount charges to be borne by beneficiary
23.description: Documentary credit discount charges are to be borne by the beneficiary.

24.description: All bank charges associated with a documentary credit other than those of the issuing bank are to be borne by the beneficiary.

ZZZ.title: Mutually defined
ZZZ.description: A code reserved for special trading partner requirements when pre-defined codes do not exist.

1.title: Clean payment
1.description: Payment under open account terms.

4.title: Documentary payment
4.description: Payment relating to a documentary settlement.

5.title: Irrevocable documentary credit
5.description: The documentary credit is irrevocable.

6.title: Revocable documentary credit
6.description: The documentary credit is revocable.

7.title: Irrevocable and transferable documentary credit
7.description: The documentary credit is irrevocable and may be transferred to a second beneficiary.

8.title: Revocable and transferable documentary credit
8.description: The documentary credit is revocable and may be transferred to a second beneficiary.

AA.title: Ship on authorization
AA.description: A delivery requirement indicating the items should not be shipped without specific authorization.

BK.title: Ship partial - balance back order
BK.description: Partial shipping is allowed. The rest of the order should be delivered as soon as possible.

CD.title: Cancel if not delivered by date
CD.description: An order or the rest of an order should be cancelled if not delivered at specified date.

DD.title: Deliver on date
DD.description: An order should be delivered exactly on specified date.

IS.title: Substitute item
IS.description: A substitute item may be delivered, if the ordered item is not available.

P2.title: Ship as soon as possible
P2.description: The order should be delivered as soon as possible.

SC.title: Ship complete order
SC.description: The order should be delivered only complete, not partial.

SF.title: Ship partial, if no freight rate increase
SF.description: Partial shipping of an order is allowed, if the total freight rate do not increase.

SP.title: Ship partial - balance cancel
SP.description: Partial shipping is allowed. The rest of the order should be cancelled.

1.title: Reception
1.description: Goods received at warehouse from another party or warehouse.

2.title: Delivery
2.description: Goods which have been delivered from the inventory to another party or warehouse.

3.title: Scrapped parts
3.description: Adjustment due to scrapped parts.

4.title: Difference
4.description: The difference between the inventory, as physically counted, and the inventory recorded by the system.

5.title: Property transfer within warehouse
5.description: An inventory movement issued when goods are moved (physically or logically) from one owner to another, whenever inventories are held in account of several owners of the same product within the same warehouse.

6.title: Inventory recycling
6.description: This inventory movement is due to recycling of goods. For instance, defective goods have been repaired and are put back to the available inventory.

7.title: Reversal of previous movement
7.description: This inventory movement is issued to cancel a previously processed movement.

8.title: Defects (technical)
8.description: This inventory movement corresponds to parts with technical defect.

9.title: Commercial
9.description: The inventory movement has been issued for commercial reasons.

10.title: Conversion
10.description: The inventory movement is due to conversion of goods.

11.title: Consumption
11.description: The inventory movement corresponds to goods taken out of consigned inventory for consumption.

1.title: Movement out of inventory
1.description: Outgoing goods.

2.title: Movement into inventory
2.description: Incoming goods.

1.title: Book-keeping inventory balance
1.description: An inventory balance resulting from the book-keeping.

2.title: Formal inventory balance
2.description: An inventory balance in accordance with the formal inventory procedure.

3.title: Interim inventory balance
3.description: An inventory balance resulting from an interim counting.

1.title: Multi-currency credit cover
1.description: Invoices in currencies other than the currency of the credit cover are expected.

2.title: Request new limit
2.description: Seller requests new limit.

3.title: Request increased limit
3.description: Seller requests increase of existing limit.

4.title: Request for preliminary assessment
4.description: Request for information to be used during negotiation with prospective clients (sellers).

5.title: Request for new account only
5.description: Request for opening new account only.

1.title: Preliminary assessment
1.description: A preliminary assessment without formal approval or commitment.

2.title: Approved
2.description: The limit request has been approved.

3.title: Not approved
3.description: The limit request has not been approved.

4.title: Conditional approval
4.description: Approval subject to conditions as specified.

5.title: Partly approved
5.description: Partly approved as specified.

6.title: Still investigating
6.description: The limit request is still under investigation.

7.title: Open new account only
7.description: Buyer account has been opened without an approved limit.

8.title: Cancellation
8.description: The existing limit has been cancelled.

9.title: Reduction
9.description: Credit limit is reduced.

1.title: Requested financial information not provided
1.description: Party requested has not provided financial information.

2.title: No financial information available
2.description: No financial information is available on buyer.

3.title: Debtor is out of business
3.description: Debtor ceased trading activities.

4.title: Debtor is new company
4.description: Debtor is newly incorporated.

5.title: Debtor is not registered
5.description: Debtor is not formally registered as legal entity.

6.title: Debtor is non-trading company
6.description: Debtor without trading, e.g. holding company.

7.title: No comment
7.description: No information can be disclosed.

8.title: Only insolvency risk covered
8.description: Only the risk of insolvency is covered.

9.title: Subject to acceptance of bill of exchange
9.description: Limit cover conditional to buyer's acceptance of bill of exchange.

10.title: Document against acceptance
10.description: Limit given on documents against acceptance terms.

11.title: Document against payment
11.description: Limit given on documents against payment terms.

12.title: Adverse information is publicly available
12.description: Adverse information on buyer is publicly available.

13.title: Credit limit full
13.description: No approval or increase in credit possible.

14.title: Lack of turnover
14.description: Limit reduced. E.g. cancelled due to absence of activity.

15.title: Other
15.description: Reasons not otherwise specified here.

1.title: Article price composition
1.description: A breakdown of the item price is requested.

2.title: Article price
2.description: The item price is requested.

3.description: Information about constituent material, such as copper and plastics, is requested.

4.title: Carrier
4.description: Suggested carrier is requested.

5.description: General conditions of sale are requested.

6.title: Delivery party
6.description: Suggested grouping centre is requested.

7.title: Economics dates
7.description: Material, labour and overheads economic dates are requested.

8.title: Lead time
8.description: Item lead time is requested.

9.title: Packaging price composition
9.description: A breakdown of the package price is requested.

10.title: Packaging details
10.description: Details about packaging is requested.

11.title: Production location
11.description: Information about which production site is going to be used is requested.

12.title: Packaging price
12.description: The packaging price is requested.

13.title: Payment terms
13.description: Payment terms are requested.

14.title: Shipment from location
14.description: Information from where the items are shipped is requested.

15.title: Tooling price composition
15.description: A breakdown of the tooling price is requested.

16.title: Tooling items details
16.description: Details about the tooling items are requested.

17.title: Tooling total details
17.description: Details about the total tooling is requested.

18.title: Validity dates
18.description: The quotations validity dates are requested.

19.title: Working pattern
19.description: Information about working week, day and shift is requested.

2.title: Add and replace
2.description: The data contains new objects, which are to be added, and existing objects, which are to replace objects which have the same identifier.

3.title: Replace
3.description: The data is to replace existing data which has the same identifier.

4.description: The data identified is to be deleted.

7.description: Maintenance operation involves change.

8.description: The item is marked for deletion in a future release.

1.title: In right condition
1.description: The seal is in right condition.

2.title: Damaged
2.description: The seal is damaged.

1.title: Destination charge totals
1.description: Code to indicate total charges levied at destination.

3.description: The total amount of the message.

4.title: Invoices total amount summary
4.description: The summary of a number of invoices' total amounts.

5.title: Amount for Customs purposes
5.description: Number of monetary units expressed in a specified currency for Customs purposes (see: 5004).

7.title: Financial transaction amount
7.description: Amount refers to financial transaction.

8.title: Total(s) of deferred items
8.description: To specify the total(s) of all deferred items from one reinsurance account.

9.title: Total(s) of open cash claims
9.description: To specify the total(s) of all open cash claims from one reinsurance account.

10.title: Reinsurance account balance
10.description: To specify the result(s) of the reinsurance account calculation.

11.title: Prepaid totals
11.description: Totals of prepaid freight and charges.

12.title: Collect totals
12.description: Totals of collect freight and charges.

14.title: Valuation amounts
14.description: Code to indicate declarations amounts.

15.title: Prepayment amount
15.description: Self explanatory.

16.title: Alternative currency total amount
16.description: Self explanatory.

17.title: Documentary credit amount
17.description: Value expressed in monetary terms of the documentary credit.

18.title: Additional amounts covered: freight costs
18.description: Freight costs are also covered under the documentary credit.

19.title: Additional amounts covered: insurance costs
19.description: Insurance costs are also covered under the documentary credit.

20.description: Interest on delayed or deferred payment is also covered under the documentary credit.

21.title: Additional amounts covered: inspection costs
21.description: Goods inspection costs are also covered under the documentary credit.

22.title: Part of documentary credit amount
22.description: Part of documentary credit subject to sight, deferred or acceptance payment when the documentary credit is available by mixed payment.

23.title: Amount of note
23.description: Amount of debit or credit note.

25.description: Totals to date.

26.description: Totals this measurement period.

27.description: Total to the end of last measurement period.

28.title: Total balance credit risk covered
28.description: The total balance of factored invoices which are covered for credit risk.

1.title: Project
1.description: Indicates that the index relates to the whole project.

2.title: Group
2.description: Indicates that the index relates to a group of work items.

3.title: Alternative
3.description: Indicates that the index is an alternative.

1.title: VAT, 1st value
1.description: First VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 1 to 3 different ways to set this value.

2.title: VAT, 2nd value
2.description: Second VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 2 or 3 different ways to set this value.

3.title: VAT, 3rd value
3.description: Third VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 3 different ways to set this value.

4.title: Additional royalties (Customs)
4.description: Royalties relating to the imported goods that the buyer must pay, either directly or indirectly, as a condition of sale, to the extent that they are not included in the price actually paid or payable.

5.title: Adjusted amount
5.description: The amount specified is the adjusted amount.

6.title: Amount reference currency
6.description: The owing amount in the currency used as reference in the transaction.

7.title: Agreed charge
7.description: Charges which parties agreed upon.

8.title: Allowance or charge amount
8.description: [5422] Total amount of allowance or charge.

9.title: Amount due/amount payable
9.description: Amount to be paid.

10.title: Amount in charge currency
10.description: Indicates that the amount is based on the charged currency.

11.title: Amount paid
11.description: Self explanatory.

12.title: Amount remitted
12.description: Amount which was remitted (see remittance advice).

13.title: Amount subject to total monetary discount
13.description: Self explanatory.

14.title: Amount target currency
14.description: The amount in the currency in which the amount is paid or has to be paid.

15.title: Average ledger balance
15.description: The addition of the balance all accounts divided by the number of accounts.

16.title: Bank release fee
16.description: Self explanatory.

17.title: Batch total
17.description: The complete quantity of anything needed for or made in one operation or lot.

18.title: Brokerage
18.description: Fee charged by a broker for acting on behalf of a third party.

19.title: Buying commission
19.description: Commission paid by the importer to his/her agent for the service of representing him/her in the purchase.

20.title: Data value on carrier media (Customs)
20.description: Value of data contained on the carrier media (e.g. magnetic tape).

21.title: Cash discount
21.description: Cash discount given by the seller to the buyer.

22.title: Cash on delivery amount
22.description: Amount to be collected by carrier upon delivery of goods. This amount represents approximately the value of the goods.

23.title: Charge amount
23.description: Self explanatory.

24.title: Charge summary total
24.description: Code to indicate the total charges relating to a consignment.

25.title: Charge/allowance basis
25.description: The amount specified is the basis for calculation of charges/allowance.

26.title: Charges collect fee
26.description: Self explanatory.

27.title: Charges in destination currency
27.description: Collect charges payable in the currency of the country of destination.

28.title: Collect charge summary total
28.description: Self explanatory.

29.title: Collect charges in destination currency
29.description: Collect charges payable in the currency of the country of destination.

30.title: Collect freight charge including VAT
30.description: This is the total amount that has to be collected from the consignee or other intermediary intervening party - Including VAT-.

31.title: Collect freight charge without VAT
31.description: For legal accounting reasons the amount without VAT has to be announced, together with the amount of VAT.

32.title: Collect other charges due agent total
32.description: Self explanatory.

33.title: Collect taxes total
33.description: Self explanatory.

34.title: Collected balance required
34.description: A certain sum of money that must be kept in an account.

35.title: Container cost
35.description: Description to be provided.

36.title: Converted amount
36.description: The amount is converted from another currency.

37.title: Credit on consignment
37.description: Credit deducted from the total invoice amount for the value of goods not included in a consignment but included in the invoice.

38.title: Invoice item amount
38.description: (5068) Total sum charged in respect of a single Invoice item in accordance with the terms of delivery.

39.title: Invoice total amount
39.description: [5444] Total sum charged in respect of one or more Invoices in accordance with the terms of delivery.

40.title: Customs value
40.description: (5032) Value declared for Customs purposes on those goods in a consignment which are subject to the same Customs procedure, and have the same tariff/statistical heading, country information and duty regime.

41.title: Assigned Customs value
41.description: Goods value assigned by Customs.

42.title: Total cash payments received by factor
42.description: Total allocated amount of cash payments received by a factor.

43.title: Declared total Customs value
43.description: [5070] Total value declared for Customs purposes of all goods in a consignment, whether or not they are subject to the same Customs procedure, or have the same tariff/statistical heading, country information, and duty regime.

44.title: Declared value for carriage
44.description: (5036) Value, declared by the shipper or his agent solely for the purpose of varying the carrier's level of liability from that provided in the contract of carriage, in case of loss or damage to goods or delayed delivery.

45.title: Deductible after importation charges (Customs)
45.description: Charges (e.g. construction, assembly, erection, maintenance or technical assistance) after importation, which are included in the total invoice price, that may be deducted to arrive at a Customs value.

46.title: Deductions (Customs)
46.description: [5020] Allowable deductions from the Customs value basis used.

48.title: Deposit total
48.description: The whole amount of money that one entrusts for safekeeping.

49.title: Development necessary for production of imported goods (Customs)
49.description: Value of engineering, development, artwork, design work and plans and sketches carried out elsewhere than in the Customs territory and necessary for the production of the imported goods.

50.title: Disbursements
50.description: Amount of disbursements to be collected by the carrier according to the order given by the shipper.

51.title: Disbursements fee
51.description: Fee charged for the collection of disbursements.

52.title: Discount amount
52.description: The amount specified is the discount amount.

56.title: Duty/tax/fee basis amount
56.description: The amount specified is the basis for duty/tax or fee.

57.title: Equivalent amount
57.description: This amount is equivalent to the amount to be transferred, but in another currency.

59.title: Fees paid year to date
59.description: Payments made for goods thus far.

60.title: Final (posted) amount
60.description: The amount posted to an account, finally, after charges/allowances.

61.title: Float (e.g. "cash float")
61.description: The status of funds in the process of collection.

62.title: Total payments on account received by a factor
62.description: Total unallocated amount of payments received by a factor.

63.title: FOB value
63.description: Identifies the value of the shipment free on board, named port of shipment (see FOB Incoterm of ICC).

64.title: Freight charge
64.description: Amount to be paid for moving goods, by whatever means, from one place to another, inclusive discounts, allowances, rebates, adjustment factors and additional cost relating to freight costs (UN/ECE Recommendation no 23).

65.title: Total indirect amount payments made to a seller or his agent instead of to a factor
65.description: Total indirect amount of payments made to a seller or his agent instead of to a factor.

66.title: Goods item total
66.description: Net price x quantity for the line item.

68.title: Insurance and transport charges (Customs)
68.description: (5488)+(5292) Sum total of transport and insurances charges (CCC).

69.title: Insurance and transport charges incurred outside Customs territory
69.description: (5488)+(5292) Insurance and transport charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

70.title: Insurance charges (Customs)
70.description: [5488] Amount of premium payable to the insurance company to insure the goods to the port or place of importation.

71.title: Insurance charges incurred outside of Customs territory
71.description: (5488) Insurance charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

72.title: Internal charges (Customs)
72.description: Charges incurred within a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

73.title: Total amount of payments booked to the collateral account
73.description: Total amount of payments booked to the collateral account.

74.title: Amount to be paid in advance
74.description: Amount which is to be paid before goods are delivered or the service is rendered.

75.title: Registered capital
75.description: Registered amount of equity of a company.

76.title: Investable balance
76.description: To put left over money in something offering profitable returns.

77.title: Invoice amount
77.description: [5068] Total sum charged in respect of a single Invoice in accordance with the terms of delivery.

78.title: Landing charges
78.description: The charges incurred in landing the goods into store in the country of importation, excluding Customs duties and taxes.

79.title: Total line items amount
79.description: The sum of all the line item amounts.

80.title: Licence fees related to imported goods (Customs)
80.description: Licence fees relating to the imported goods that the buyer must pay, either directly or indirectly, as a condition of sale, to the extent that they are not included in the price actually paid or payable.

81.title: Loading and handling cost
81.description: Cost incurred by loading and handling.

82.title: Lock box total
82.description: The complete amount of funds that customers mailed in to a specific location. Often times funds are sent to a post- office lock box in their city.

83.title: Lumpsum
83.description: An agreed sum of money, which is paid in full at one time. This term is often used in connection with charter parties.

84.title: Material consumed in production of imported goods (Customs)
84.description: Value of materials consumed in the production of the imported goods.

88.title: National preference basis amount
88.description: Amount giving the basis for national preference calculation.

89.title: Negative collected balance
89.description: Having a quantity of less than zero in an account.

90.title: Negative ledger balance
90.description: For an asset account, this would be when the account had a credit balance. For liability and owner's equity accounts, it would be when the account had a debit balance.

91.title: Net adjustment
91.description: The end-of-the-period total amount which is left after recording appropriate adjusting entries.

92.title: Net fee position
92.description: The payments left over after deductions or allowances have been made.

93.title: Net year to date excess (deficit)
93.description: A negative amount of an item.

94.title: No amount of insurance
94.description: No amount of insurance has been declared for a consignment.

95.title: No declared value for carriage
95.description: No value has been declared for purposes of carriage.

96.title: No declared value for Customs
96.description: No value has been declared for Customs purposes.

98.title: Original amount
98.description: Original amount, without charges, allowances or adjustment.

99.title: Other charges at destination
99.description: Code to indicate charges levied at destination.

100.title: Other charges due agent
100.description: Code to indicate that certain charges accrue to an agent.

101.title: Other charges due carrier
101.description: Code to indicate that certain charges accrue to a carrier.

102.title: Other commissions
102.description: Other commissions paid by the importer to his/her agent in relation to the goods being imported.

103.title: Other deductible charges
103.description: Other charges deducted from the total invoice value.

105.title: Other valuation charges (Customs)
105.description: Other valuation charges which are payable by reason of the importation or sale of the goods in the Customs territory.

106.title: Packing cost
106.description: Cost for packing concerning labour and/or material.

107.title: Packing cost (Customs)
107.description: [5448] Costs incurred for all containers and coverings of whatever nature which are considered as being one for Customs purposes with the goods, and the cost of packing whether for labour or material.

108.title: Parts incorporated in imported goods (Customs)
108.description: Materials, components, parts and similar items incorporated in the imported goods.

110.title: Pick-up fee
110.description: Fee incurring if item has been or will be picked up.

111.title: Positive collected balance
111.description: Having a quantity of greater than zero in an account.

112.title: Positive ledger balance
112.description: For an asset account, this would be when the account had a debit balance. For liability and owner's equity accounts, it would be when the account had a credit balance.

113.title: Prepaid amount
113.description: (5302) Amount which has been prepaid in advance.

116.title: Purchase amount
116.description: The cost of buying goods or services.

117.title: Quantity discount
117.description: Discount given for purchase of goods in bulk.

119.title: Received amount
119.description: The amount is what the bank received, and the one before charges/allowances.

120.title: Sales tax
120.description: Identifies the amount of sales tax payable.

121.title: Shipment value in domestic currency
121.description: The cost of transportation in domestic currency.

122.title: Specific amount payable
122.description: Amount that the consignor agrees to be invoiced or to pay. This amount is part of the total charges applied to the consignment.

123.title: Statistical value
123.description: [5218] Value declared for statistical purposes of those goods in a consignment which have the same statistical heading and country of origin.

124.title: Tax amount
124.description: Tax imposed by government or other official authority related to the weight/volume charge or valuation charge.

127.title: Tools used in production of imported goods (Customs)
127.description: Tools, dies, moulds and similar items used in the production of the imported goods.

128.title: Total amount
128.description: The amount specified is the total amount.

129.title: Total amount subject to payment discount
129.description: Part of the invoice amount which is subject to payment discount.

130.title: Total charge due
130.description: Total amount of charges payable to the carrier.

131.title: Total charges/allowances
131.description: The amount specified is the total of all charges/allowances.

133.title: Total collect charges at destination
133.description: Total charges to be collected at destination.

135.title: Total freight due
135.description: Total amount of freight costs payable to the carrier.

136.title: Total invoice additional amount
136.description: (5140) Amount to be added to the sum of invoice line amounts to arrive at the total invoice amount.

139.title: Total payment amount
139.description: A complete charge for goods or services rendered.

140.title: Total service charge
140.description: The complete payment owed to one who has performed work for another.

141.title: Cost, insurance and freight (CIF) value
141.description: Identifies the value of cost, insurance and freight. (Refer to ICC Incoterm CIF for an expanded definition).

142.title: Trade discount
142.description: Discount given to any purchaser at a particular commercial level e.g. at wholesale or retail level.

143.title: Transfer amount
143.description: The amount which has been transferred from buyer to the sellers bank.

144.title: Transport charges (Customs)
144.description: (5292) Cost incurred by shipper in moving goods, by whatever means, from one place to another under the terms of the contract of carriage, see UN/ECE Recommendation No 23. Synonym: freight charges (Customs).

145.title: Transport charges incurred outside Customs territory
145.description: (5292) Transport charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

146.title: Unit price
146.description: (5110) Reporting monetary amount is a "per unit" amount.

147.title: Acceptable quotation fluctuation amount
147.description: The maximum increase or decrease in constituent material fluctuation which will not result in an item price renegotiation.

148.title: Total payments under guarantee
148.description: Total amount paid under guarantee, such as under a factor's guarantee.

149.title: Valuation charge
149.description: A charge based on the value of goods or cargo.

150.title: Value added tax
150.description: [5490] Amount in national currency resulting from the application, at the appropriate rate, of value added tax (or similar tax) to the invoice amount subject to such tax.

151.title: Value insured
151.description: Representation in figures of the total sum covered by an insurance for a particular shipment.

152.title: Subsequent resale of imported goods (Customs)
152.description: Value of any part of the proceeds of any subsequent resale, disposal or use of the imported goods that accrues, directly or indirectly, to the seller.

153.title: Weight charge
153.description: A charge based on the weight of goods or cargo.

155.title: Standard duty
155.description: Standard Customs duty that would apply if special provisions did not apply.

156.title: G-Amount
156.description: Amount out of total invoice amount being paid into a blocked account.

157.title: Insurance value
157.description: (5010) Value for which the goods are insured.

158.title: Insurance and transport charges incurred inside Customs territory
158.description: (5488)+(5292) Charges to be paid for moving goods, by whatever means, from the point of entry into the Customs territory (within a Customs union: to the point of entry in the final destination country).

159.title: Licence (value deducted)
159.description: Amount in the currency of the licence to be written off from the total licence value.

160.title: Other costs

AAA.title: Calculation net
AAA.description: The price stated is the net price including allowances/ charges. Allowances/charges may be stated for information only.

AAB.title: Calculation gross
AAB.description: The price stated is the gross price to which allowances/ charges must be applied.

AAC.title: Allowances and charges not included, tax included
AAC.description: The price does not include the allowances and charges, but includes the taxes.

AAD.title: Average selling price
AAD.description: Average selling price of a product.

AAE.title: Information price, excluding allowances or charges, including taxes
AAE.description: The price stated is for information purposes only and excludes all allowances and charges. Taxes however are included in the price.

AAF.title: Information price, excluding allowances or charges, and taxes
AAF.description: The price stated is for information purposes only and excludes all allowances, charges and taxes.

AAG.title: Additive unit price component
AAG.description: A code to indicate that the price described is an additive component of the total price.

CAL.title: Calculation price
CAL.description: The price stated is the price for the calculation of the line item amount.

INF.title: Information
INF.description: The price is provided for information.

INV.title: Invoice price
INV.description: Referenced price taken from an invoice.

AAB.title: Provisional countervailing duty cash
AAB.description: Countervailing duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of subsidization by Customs.

AAC.title: Provisional countervailing duty bond
AAC.description: Countervailing duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on subsidization by Customs.

AAD.title: Tobacco tax
AAD.description: A tax levied on tobacco products.

ADD.title: Anti-dumping duty
ADD.description: Duty applied to goods ruled to have been dumped in an import market at a price lower than that in the exporter's domestic market.

BOL.title: Stamp duty (Imposta di Bollo)
BOL.description: Tax required in Italy, which may be fixed or graduated in various circumstances (e.g. VAT exempt documents or bank receipts).

CAP.title: Agricultural levy
CAP.description: Levy imposed on agricultural products where there is a difference between the selling price between trading countries.

CST.title: Commodity specific tax
CST.description: Tax related to a specified commodity, e.g. illuminants, salts.

CUD.title: Customs duty
CUD.description: Duties laid down in the Customs tariff, to which goods are liable on entering or leaving the Customs territory (CCC).

CVD.title: Countervailing duty
CVD.description: A duty on imported goods applied for compensate for subsidies granted to those goods in the exporting country.

ENV.title: Environmental tax
ENV.description: Tax assessed for funding or assuring environmental protection or clean-up.

EC.title: Excise duty
EC.description: Customs or fiscal authorities code to identify a specific or ad valorem levy on a specific commodity, applied either domestically or at time of importation.

EP.title: Agricultural export rebate
EP.description: Monetary rebate given to the seller in certain circumstances when agricultural products are exported.

FET.title: Federal excise tax
FET.description: Tax levied by the federal government on the manufacture of specific items.

GST.title: Goods and services tax
GST.description: Tax levied on the final consumption of goods and services throughout the production and distribution chain.

LAC.title: Business license fee
LAC.description: Government assessed charge for permit to do business.

LDP.title: Light dues payable
LDP.description: Fee levied on a vessel to pay for port navigation lights.

LOC.title: Local sales taxes
LOC.description: Assessment charges on sale of goods or services by city, borough country or other taxing authorities below state/provincial level.

LST.title: Lust tax
LST.description: Tax imposed for clean-up of leaky underground storage tanks.

MCA.title: Monetary compensatory amount
MCA.description: Levy on Common Agricultural Policy (EC) goods used to compensate for fluctuating currencies between member states.

MCD.title: Miscellaneous cash deposit
MCD.description: Duty paid and held on deposit, by Customs, during an investigation period prior to a final decision being made on any aspect related to imported goods (except valuation) by Customs.

PDB.title: Provisional duty bond
PDB.description: Anti-dumping duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on dumping by Customs.

PDC.title: Provisional duty cash
PDC.description: Anti-dumping duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of dumping by Customs.

SSS.title: Shifted social securities
SSS.description: Social securities share of the invoice amount to be paid directly to the social securities collector.

STT.title: State/provincial sales tax
STT.description: All applicable sale taxes by authorities at the state or provincial level, below national level.

SUP.title: Suspended duty
SUP.description: Duty suspended or deferred from payment.

SUR.title: Surtax
SUR.description: A tax or duty applied on and in addition to existing duties and taxes.

SWT.title: Shifted wage tax
SWT.description: Wage tax share of the invoice amount to be paid directly to the tax collector(s office).

TO.title: Turnover tax
TO.description: Tax levied on the total sales/turnover of a corporation.

TTA.title: Tonnage taxes
TTA.description: Tax levied based on the vessel's net tonnage.

VAD.title: Valuation deposit
VAD.description: Duty paid and held on deposit, by Customs, during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on valuation of the goods being made.

VAT.title: Value added tax
VAT.description: A tax on domestic or imported goods applied to the value added at each stage in the production/distribution cycle.

1.title: Handling commission
1.description: Fee for the processing of documentary credit, collection and payment which are charged to the customer.

2.title: Amendment commission
2.description: Fee for amendments in documentary credit and collection business (not extensions and increases of documentary credits).

3.title: Acceptance commission
3.description: Fee for the acceptance of draft in documentary credit and collection business which are drawn on us (also to be seen as a kind of 'guarantee commission').

4.title: Commission for obtaining acceptance
4.description: Fee for obtaining an acceptance under collections on the basis of 'documents against acceptance'.

5.title: Commission on delivery
5.description: Fee for delivery of documents without corresponding payment.

6.title: Advising commission
6.description: Fee for advising documentary credits (charged also in case of confirmed credits).

7.title: Confirmation commission
7.description: Fee for confirmation of credit.

8.title: Deferred payment commission
8.description: Fee for the deferred payment period under documentary credits confirmed by bank. This fee are charges for the period from presentation of the document until due date of payment.

9.title: Commission for taking up documents
9.description: Fee charged to the foreign bank for the processing of documentary credit.

10.title: Opening commission
10.description: Fee for opening revocable documentary credit.

11.title: Fee for payment under reserve
11.description: Fee charged to the customer for discrepancies in credit documents in the case of which the bank have to stipulate payment under reserve.

12.title: Discrepancy fee
12.description: Fee charged to the foreign bank for discrepancies in credit documents.

13.title: Domicilation commission
13.description: Fee for the domicilation of bills with the bank.

14.title: Commission for release of goods
14.description: Commission for the release of goods sent to the bank.

15.title: Collection commission
15.description: Fee for settling collections on the basis of 'documents against payments'.

16.title: Negotiation commission
16.description: Fee for the purchase of documents under sight credit for the first ten days.

17.title: Return commission
17.description: Fee for cheques, bills and collections returned unpaid and/or recalled.

18.title: B/L splitting charges
18.description: Fee for the splitting of bills of lading.

19.title: Trust commission
19.description: Fee for the handling on a fiduciary basis of imported goods that have been warehoused.

20.title: Transfer commission
20.description: Fee for the transfer of transferable documentary credits.

21.title: Commission for opening irrevocable doc. credits
21.description: Fee for opening irrevocable documentary credits. This fee is a kind of 'Guarantee commission' as compensation for the commitment into which the bank have entered on the customers behalf; similar to confirmation commission, acceptance commission.

22.title: Pre-advice commission
22.description: Fee for the pre-advice of a documentary credit.

23.title: Supervisory commission
23.description: Fee for the supervising unconfirmed documentary credits with a deferred payment period.

24.title: Model charges
24.description: Fee for decoding telex messages.

25.title: Risk commission
25.description: Commission in addition to the confirmation commission for documentary credits from sensitive countries.

26.title: Guarantee commission
26.description: Commission for drawing up guaranties.

27.title: Reimbursement commission
27.description: Fee for reimbursement of, for example, documentary credits.

28.title: Stamp duty
28.description: Tax payable on bills in accordance with national bill of exchange legislations.

29.title: Brokerage
29.description: Brokers commission arising, in trade with foreign currencies.

30.title: Bank charges
30.description: Charges deducted/claimed by other banks involved in the transaction.

31.title: Bank charges information
31.description: Charges not included in the total charge amount i.e. the charges are for information only.

32.title: Courier fee
32.description: Fee for use of courier service.

33.title: Phone fee
33.description: Fee for use of phone.

34.title: Postage fee
34.description: Fee for postage.

35.title: S.W.I.F.T. fee
35.description: Fee for use of S.W.I.F.T.

36.title: Telex fee
36.description: Fee for telex.

51.description: Unit charge per unused credit cover.

2.description: Charges calculated by the carrier for specific events like re-weighting, re-loading, unexpected operations, services required during the voyage, etc.

3.description: Transport charges plus Additional charges (e.g. for re- loading, re-weighting or unexpected operations) that must be precised in the payment conditions by the consignor (other charges must be taken in account by the consignee).

4.description: The basic freight payable on the cargo as per tariff.

5.title: Destination haulage charges
5.description: Self explanatory.

6.description: Sums paid out by ship's agent at a port and recovered from the carrier.

7.title: Destination port charges

9.description: Transport charges to be paid by the consignor for a part of the voyage, i.e. up to a location that must be precised.

10.title: Origin port charges

11.title: Origin haulage charges

12.title: Other charges
12.description: Self explanatory.

15.description: All amounts to be paid by the consignor for a part of the voyage, i.e. up to a location that must be precised. (The remaining part of the voyage to be paid by the consignee) The amounts are calculated by the carrier in accordance with tariffs or in case of special events during the voyage (e.g. rail - freight costs - additional costs).

16.description: Code to indicate weight/valuation charges to be either wholly prepaid or wholly collect.

17.title: All costs

18.title: Transport costs and supplementary costs
18.description: Description to be provided.
