ADR.title: European agreement on the international carriage of dangerous goods on road (ADR)
ADR.description: European agreement on the international carriage of dangerous goods on road. ADR is the abbreviation of "Accord europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises dangereuses par route".

AGS.title: DE, ADR and GGVS combined regulations for combined transport
AGS.description: Combined German and European regulations for the transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European roads. ADR means: Accord Europeen relatif au Transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route. GGVS means: Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse.

ANR.title: ADNR, Autorisation de transport de matieres Dangereuses pour la Navigation sur le Rhin
ANR.description: Regulations for dangerous goods transportation on the Rhine.

ARD.title: DE, ARD and RID - Combined regulations for combined transport
ARD.description: Combined European regulations for the combined transportation of dangerous goods on roads and rails. ARD means: Autorisation de transport par Route de matieres dangereuses. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer.

CFR.title: 49 code of federal regulations
CFR.description: US federal regulations issued by the US Dept. of transportation covering the domestic transportation of dangerous goods by truck, rail, water and air.

COM.title: DE, ADR, RID, GGVS and GGVE - Combined regulations for combined transport
COM.description: Combined German and European regulations for the combined transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European roads and rails. ADR means: Accord Europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuse par Route. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer. GGVS means: Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse. GGVE means: Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn.

GVE.title: DE, GGVE (Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn)
GVE.description: German regulation for the transportation of dangerous goods on rail.

GVS.title: DE, GGVS (Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse)
GVS.description: German regulation for the transportation of dangerous goods on road.

ICA.title: IATA ICAO
ICA.description: Regulations covering the international transportation of dangerous goods issued by the International Air Transport Association and the International Civil Aviation Organization.

IMD.title: IMO IMDG code
IMD.description: Regulations regarding the transportation of dangerous goods on ocean-going vessels issued by the International Maritime Organization.

RGE.title: DE, RID and GGVE, Combined regulations for combined transport on rails
RGE.description: Combined German and European regulations for the transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European rails. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer. GGVE means: Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn.

RID.title: Railroad dangerous goods book (RID)
RID.description: International regulations concerning the international  carriage of dangerous goods by rail. RID is the abbreviation of "Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer".

9.title: Cleared export restrictions
9.description: Goods/consignments/equipment held prior to loading have now been cleared for export.

10.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been held prior to shipment and are now cleared for shipment following examination by relevant authority.

11.title: Cleared by port authority
11.description: The port authority has given permission for the goods/consignments/equipment/means of transport to leave the port.

12.title: Cleared by customs
12.description: Customs have cleared goods/consignments for import/export.

13.title: Collected
13.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been collected from a predetermined location.

14.title: Completed
14.description: The process has been completed.

15.title: Consolidated
15.description: Goods/consignments have been added to other goods/ consignments to form a larger consignment and/or have been incorporated into one or more containers/units.

16.title: Crossed border
16.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have crossed a border from one country to another.

17.title: Customs refusal
17.description: The Customs authorities have refused to clear the goods/consignments/equipment.

18.title: Damaged
18.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been damaged in the course of transportation.

19.title: Damaged equipment quoted
19.description: Damaged equipment has been assessed and the quotation sent to lessor.

20.title: Delayed
20.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been delayed in the course of transportation.

21.title: Delivered
21.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been delivered to a location/party in the transport chain.

22.title: Delivery completed
22.description: Delivery of the goods/consignments/equipment has been completed as per instructions.

23.title: Delivery not completed
23.description: Delivery of the goods/consignments/equipment has not been completed in accordance with instructions.

24.title: Departed
24.description: The means of transport has departed from a location in the transport chain.

25.title: Departure delay
25.description: The transport has been delayed in departing on the arranged transport action.

26.title: Deramped
26.description: Equipment has been removed from a position above other equipment on a means of transport.

27.title: Despatched
27.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have departed from a location in the transport chain.

28.title: Stripped
28.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been unloaded from equipment in which they were transported.

29.title: Discharged
29.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been unloaded from a means of transport.

30.title: Empty on inspection
30.description: The package/equipment has been found to be empty.

31.title: En route
31.description: The goods/consignments/equipment are in the normal course of transportation to the next destination.

32.title: Equipment in from repair
32.description: A piece of equipment has been received in after having been sent out for repair.

33.title: Equipment out for repair
33.description: A piece of equipment has been sent out for repair.

34.title: Equipment repaired
34.description: A damaged piece of equipment has been repaired.

35.title: Expedited to destination
35.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been expedited to the next/final destination in the transport chain.

36.title: Not found
36.description: The goods/consignments/equipment notified to be missing have not been located.

37.title: Found
37.description: The goods/consignments/equipment previously notified missing have now been located.

38.title: Freight paid
38.description: The freight charges on goods/consignments/equipment have been paid.

39.title: From bond
39.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been moved/are available to be moved from bond.

40.title: Goods/consignments/equipment at port
40.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have arrived/are available at port.

41.title: Handover
41.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been formally passed from one point in the transport chain to another under responsibility of the same transporter. (See also 'handover delivered'.)

42.title: Handover delivered
42.description: The goods/consignments/equipment from one transport operator have been passed to another transport operator. (see also 'handover'.)

43.title: Handover received
43.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been received by one transport operator from another transport operator.

44.title: Ill-routed consignment reforwarded
44.description: The goods/consignments/equipment which were previously sent to a wrong destination are on the way to correct destination.

45.title: Informed Consignee of arrival
45.description: The consignee has been informed formally of the arrival at a transit or final destination of goods/consignments/equipment.

46.title: Into bond
46.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been moved/is available to be moved into bond.

47.title: Into packing depot
47.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been moved into a LCL (less than container load)/packing depot.

48.title: Loaded
48.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been loaded onto a means of transport.

49.title: Lost
49.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been lost in the course of a movement along the transport chain.

50.title: Manifested
50.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been included on the list of units moving from one location to another in the transport chain.

51.title: Means of transport damaged
51.description: The means of transport on which the goods/consignments/equipment was being (was to be) moved has been damaged.

52.title: Mechanical breakdown
52.description: There has been a mechanical breakdown of the means of transport/equipment on which the goods/consignments/equipment was being (was to be) moved.

53.title: No pick-up
53.description: The goods/consignments/equipment expected to be picked up and conveyed from location to location in the transport chain have not been picked up.

54.title: Not identified
54.description: The goods/consignments/equipment expected to be located and identified in the transport chain cannot be identified.

55.title: Not collected
55.description: The goods/consignments/equipment expected to be collected after transportation have not been collected.

56.title: Not delivered
56.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have not been delivered.

57.title: Not loaded
57.description: The goods/consignments/equipment to be loaded onto a means of transport have not been loaded on the expected transport.

58.title: Off hire
58.description: Equipment previously under hire to a customer has been returned to the lessor and the contract has been terminated.

59.title: Off loaded
59.description: The goods/consignments/equipment previously loaded to a means of transport have been removed from that means of transport before completion of the planned transport.

60.title: On hire
60.description: Equipment has been hired out to a hirer/customer.

61.title: Outstanding claims settled
61.description: Outstanding claims in respect of goods/consignments/equipment have been settled.

62.title: Over landed
62.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been discharged from a means of transport at a specific location when they were not expected to be discharged.

63.title: Package not ready
63.description: The package was not available for collection.

65.title: Plugged equipment
65.description: Equipment, e.g. a refrigerated container, has been plugged into the power source.

67.title: Positioned goods/consignments/equipment
67.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been positioned on a means of transport.

68.title: Pre-informed
68.description: The consignor/consignee has been advised in advance of a transport action.

69.title: Put to refuse
69.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been written off and disposed of.

70.title: Ramped equipment
70.description: Equipment has been placed above other equipment and placed on a means of transport.

71.title: Ready for transportation
71.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been made ready for transportation.

72.title: Receipt fully acknowledged
72.description: The consignee has given full acknowledgement for the receipt of goods.

73.title: Receipt partially acknowledged
73.description: The consignee has not given full acknowledgement for the receipt of goods.

74.title: Received

75.title: Reconsigned
75.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been consigned to a party other than the original or subsequent consignees.

76.title: Reforwarding on request
76.description: The goods/consignments/equipment which have been delayed will be/have been reforwarded on request by appropriate authority.

77.title: Refused without reason given
77.description: The transport action/documentation has been refused without explanation.

78.title: Released
78.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been released to an authorized party.

79.title: Reloaded
79.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been reloaded onto a means of transport.

80.title: Returned as instructed
80.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been returned to a location as per instructions.

81.title: Returned as wreck

82.title: Returned
82.description: Goods/consignments/equipment have been returned to a previous location.

83.title: Sealed equipment

84.title: Service ordered
84.description: A service has been ordered in relation to the transportation of goods/consignments/equipment.

85.title: Short landed
85.description: Goods/consignments/equipment expected to be discharged from a means of transport at a specific location have not been discharged.

86.title: Short shipped

87.title: Sorted wrong route

88.title: Split

90.title: Stopped

91.title: Stored
91.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been stored at a location.

92.title: Stowed

93.title: Stuffed
93.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been loaded into a piece of equipment, e.g. a container.

94.title: Stuffed and sealed

55.description: The consignment of goods has been split into two or more consignments.

58.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been delayed in transit.

61.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been stowed under/below deck.

64.description: The goods/consignments/equipment have been in a storage facility for longer than permitted free time.
